Description: The VIS assembly mounts a complete orbital imaging package comprised of a UV spectrometer for atmospheric analysis, IR spectrometer for surface analysis, and a compact low-res Telescope camera for pretty pictures in the visual range. There are two mounting options: 30 degrees for use with Vorona, and 90 degrees for use with other designs and surfaces. Toggle with the right-click menu. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: ca_vor_comm
Title: CAE-A03 Vorona Communication Array
Description: Vorona's Comm Array mounts dual conic antennae for short range, low-gain communication. The system also has a mount for a high-gain dish, designed for the Vorona CAE-102 dish (Sold separately). (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: ca_vor_core
Title: CAE-200 'Vorona'
Description: The Vorona probe system is designed to work in tandem with a Fomalhaut lander to conduct simultaneous orbital/surface science. It packs batteries, avionics, and monopropellant in a very rugged case. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: ca_vor_dish
Title: CAE-102 Vorona Dish Antenna
Description: The Vorona dish has a powerful transmitter for its size, that should allow a fair bit of range in communication in the inner solar system; whether you want it to or not. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: ca_vor_engine
Title: KTDU-425A
Description: A gas generator hypergolic vacuum engine designed for use in the 3MV, 4MV and 5MV spacecraft buses of the Mars and Venera probes.

Name: ca_vor_mag
Title: CAE-MG03 Magnetometer
Description: This is a really high-tech dowsing rod that detects and measures magnetic fields. For H2O dowsing rods, contact the Coatl Horticulture department. Any claims that dowsing is pseudo-science are imaginative, or fictitious. Any resemblance to actual claims, proven or not, are purely coincidental. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: ca_vor_mptank
Title: CAE-MT12 Propellant Tank (Pressurized)
Description: A generic, radially attached high pressure propellant tank.

Name: ca_vor_sar
Title: CAE-SAR15 Synthetic-Aperture Radar System
Description: Our Synthetic-Aperture Radar System can provide better altimeter and even more resource data than comparable "100% Organic-Aperture Radar" alternatives, don't fall for the hype! The two cone antennae can provide short-range communication. Contains no additives. Proudly using only use free-range plastics and metals during manufacturing. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: ca_vor_sep1
Title: CAE-D13-F Stack Decoupler
Description: Takes two pieces for connect together and after not when you want to not have together more. Many quality part made in Kaiwan! (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: ca_vor_sp
Title: CAE-E600-A Vorona Solar-Thermal System
Description: Vorona's wings hold large panels of photovoltaic cells as well as a large radiator for the cooling system. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: ca_vor_sp2
Title: CAE-E300 Vorona Solar-Thermal System
Description: This alternate assembly of Vorona's photovoltaic cells excludes the outer panels for missions requiring less power (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: ca_vor_tank
Title: 4MV-1/2 Spacecraft Bus Propellant Tank
Description: The main pressurized propellant storage compartment of the 4MV-1/2 spacecraft bus.

Name: ca-upgrade
Title: CA-Upgrade
Description: CA-Upgrade (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: CanardController
Title: Standard Canard
Description: Our engineers had a stroke of inspiration after "visiting" the Kerlington production facilities. Introducing our new controllable canards. Warning, hard maneuvering may cause unintended stage separation.

Name: capacitor-0625
Title: CAR-1.6K Capacitor Bank
Description: An inline capacitor for small probes. Charges slowly - activate for a large, short duration charge.

Name: capacitor-125
Title: CAR-8K Capacitor Bank
Description: By mounting six enhanced CAP-102s on a central mount, a decently sized inline capacitor bank can be created. Additionally, it can easily blow out all of the lights at the KSC!

Name: capacitor-25
Title: CAR-EXTRA Capacitor Bank
Description: This is a potent capacitor bank, which can dump enough charge to run even the largest of engines for oh, up to 10 seconds.

Name: capacitor-rad-0625
Title: CAP-101 Capacitor
Description: The CAP-101 is a radially attachable discharge capacitor. Through slow to charge up, when triggered, it will rapidly deposit its stored charge into your Electric Charge banks.

Name: capacitor-rad-0625-2
Title: CAP-106 Capacitor
Description: The CAP-106 is a more powerful radial capacitor using three of those new CAP-3A units. They're slightly flattened due to being stacked under a few boxes of Mainsails.

Name: CHAKAKWsrbGlobeIz
Title: GEM 60
Description: The 60-inch (1.5-meter) diameter GEM 60 is used on the Delta IV in sets of two or four. When two boosters are used, both are equipped with thrust vector control (TVC). When four are used, two boosters use TVC while the other two use fixed nozzles to reduce weight. Burn time 90 seconds. Diameter: [1.52 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: CHAKAOME2
Title: AJ10-190
Description: Low thrust pressure-fed hypergolic engine. It was used on the Space Shuttle for orbital insertion, maneuvering and deorbiting. Currently used by the Orion MPCV. Diameter: [1.17 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: CHAKAradialDecoupler
Title: TT-38L Radial Decoupler
Description: Explosive cord decoupler for side mounted boosters. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0, RO IN PROGRESS)

Name: chakaradialDecoupler1-2
Title: TT-70L Radial Decoupler
Description: Explosive cord decoupler for side mounted boosters. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0, RO IN PROGRESS)

Name: CHT400_Block
Title: CHT-400 Thruster Block
Description: Since 1996 the CHT-400 thruster block has been used on all Ariane 5 G, GS and ES versions for the roll and attitude control manoeuvres.

Name: CHT400_Thruster
Title: CHT-400 Monopropellant Thruster (400N)
Description: The CHT-400 thruster is primarily used for the attitude and roll control of the Ariane 5 launch vehicle during its ascent. The thruster can also be used for re-entry attitude control applications as successfully demonstrated during ARD mission. CHT-400 thrusters are also the decent engines for the ExoMars Schiaparelli Lander, nine of the thrusters fire to control the lander in the final decent to the martian surface. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: CircularIntake
Title: Circular Intake
Description: A proper turbofan intake, not only provides oxygen to air breathing engines, it pulls in twice as much air than those puny air scoops from Vac-Co. Optimized for subsonic flight.

Name: commDish
Title: Communotron 88-88
Description: Expands to a very wide (4.75m) dish. Low power, high bandwidth, good for Jupiter and a little beyond.

Name: cone05ra
Title: AIES 1.25m RA Nose Cone
Description: This nose cone was thoroughly tested to achieve the best ever aerodynamic properties.

Name: conenoseram
Title: AIES 2.5m RAM Nose Cone
Description: Gives more pleasing appearance to the side tanks and boosters.

Name: crewCabin
Title: Habitation Module
Description: This non-controllable module is designed for space stations and very large, long-range spacecraft. It can be stocked with ample consumables, and provides toilets, showers and living quarters for up to four crewmembers. There are no bunks in space, however  instead, sleeping bags are strapped to the internal walls of the module.

Name: cryoengine-125-1
Title: Vulcain Series
Description: 1990s high TWR, atmospheric and vacuum use. Vulcain is a gas-generator sustainer engine used on Ariane 5 and intended to be used on Ariane 6. Diameter: [2.1 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: cryoengine-125-2
Title: RL10B-2
Description: 1990s low-medium TWR, vacuum use. Developed for the Delta Cryogenic Second Stage (DCSS), which was first used on the Delta III then modified for the Delta IV. Its extending nozzle increases specific impulse compared to the RL10A, at the cost of greater dry mass. Boeing purchased a large number of these engines for the Delta IV, but the launcher's low flight rate led to ULA converting many of them to RL10C-1 engines for use on the Atlas V's Centaur upper stage.  min stage diameter 2.0m Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: cryoengine-25-1
Title: LE-7 Series
Description: 1990s medium TWR, atmospheric and vacuum use. Fuel-rich staged combustion engines used on the core stage of H-II series launchers. The original LE-7 was replaced by the LE-7A, which sacrificed some performance in favor of reduced cost and better reliability. Diameter: [3.0 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: cryoengine-25-2
Title: J-2X
Description: 2000s medium TWR, vacuum engine. The J-2X was intended to be used on the upper stages of Ares I and Ares V. Development continued after the cancellation of Ares, and early designs of SLS incorporated the engine, but selection of the RL10-powered Exploration Upper Stage resulted in the project being mothballed. Diameter: [3.0 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: cryoengine-375-1
Title: RS-68 Series
Description: 1990s Medium TWR atmospheric engine. Using technology developed for the Space Shuttle SSME, the RS-68 is a single-use engine, featuring a simplified design with less parts and an easier construction. The RS-68 powers the Delta IV launch vehicle family and is the most powerful LH2/LOX engine ever flown. Exhaust from the gas generator is used for roll control. Diameter: [2.43 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: cryoengine-375-2
Title: RD-0120
Description: 1980s medium TWR, atmospheric and vacuum use. The RD-0120 is a fuel-rich staged combustion engine developed to power the core stage of the Energia launcher. Diameter: [2.6 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: cryoseperator-25
Title: M-2 Cryogenic Gas Separator
Description: This impressive looking collection of pipes collects local atmosphere and uses a bunch of voodoo to separate it into useful gases, like Argon and Xenon. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: CryoXBig
Title: CryoX XXL Propellant Tank
Description: The first ever product line from Kool Kerbal Products Inc, the CryoX series is mostly guaranteed to keep your cryogenic fuels chilled until the end of time.

Name: CryoXendButt
Title: CryoX Butt Propellant Tank
Description: The first ever product line from Kool Kerbal Products Inc, the CryoX series is mostly guaranteed to keep your cryogenic fuels chilled until the end of time.

Name: CryoXmed
Title: CryoX XL Propellant Tank
Description: The first ever product line from Kool Kerbal Products Inc, the CryoX series is mostly guaranteed to keep your cryogenic fuels chilled until the end of time.

Name: CryoXnoseCone
Title: CryoX Nose Propellant Tank
Description: The first ever product line from Kool Kerbal Products Inc, the CryoX series is mostly guaranteed to keep your cryogenic fuels chilled until the end of time.

Name: CryoXsmall
Title: CryoX L Propellant Tank
Description: The first ever product line from Kool Kerbal Products Inc, the CryoX series is mostly guaranteed to keep your cryogenic fuels chilled until the end of time.

Name: CST-100?capsule
Title: CST-100 Command Module
Description: The command module of the CST-100 "Starliner" Commercial Crew Transportation System (COTS). Designed to be reusable for up to 10 times.

Name: CST-100?Heat?Shield
Title: CST-100 Heat Shield
Description: The heat shield for CST-100 "Starliner" command module.

Name: CST-100?Service?Module
Title: CST-100 Service Module
Description: The service module for the CST-100 "Starliner" spacecraft.

Name: cstNoseCone
Title: CST-100 Nose Cone
Description: A protective nose cone for the NASA Docking System of the CST-100 Starliner.

Name: cstparachute
Title: CST-100 Parachute Pack
Description: The parachute pack for the CST-100 "Starliner" command module.

Name: cupola
Title: Cupola Observatory Module
Description: Sporting large panes of transparent aluminum ceramic composite, the Cupola gives an unmatched view of space. ESA pioneered the design for the ISS, where it was attached in 2010 after launching on STS-130.

Name: CXA_ACBM
Title: Common Berthing Mechanism (Active)
Description: 1.25m Common Berthing Mechanism intended to mate with passive counterparts.

Name: CXA_APAS_A
Title: CX NASA Docking System (Active)
Description: Androgynous Peripheral Attach System intended to mate with passive counterparts. Equipped with a deployable capture ring to dampen impact.

Name: CXA_APAS_A_L04F
Title: CX NASA Docking System (Active)
Description: Androgynous Peripheral Attach System intended to mate with passive counterparts. Equipped with a deployable capture ring to dampen impact. L04F variant compatible with Tantares.

Name: CXA_APAS_P
Title: CX NASA Docking System (Passive)
Description: Androgynous Peripheral Attach System intended to mate with active counterparts.

Name: CXA_APAS_P_WB
Title: CX NASA Docking System (Passive)
Description: Androgynous Peripheral Attach System intended to mate with active counterparts. This variant has a wider base to conform with the Mk1-2 nose.

Name: CXA_EETCS
Title: Electronic Equipment Thermal Control System (EETCS)
Description: A deployable thermal control system consisting of multiple liquid cooled radiator panels.

Name: CXA_Effector
Title: Grapple Effector
Description: Effector for use to latch onto grapple fixtures. Used like a tiny docking port. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: CXA_ELM_MiniLab
Title: Experiment Logistics Module (ELM)
Description: |2M Series Science Module| Tight on space or funds? Still want high efficiency data to science conversion? The ELM is a pocket-sized science module that can be used to give just a bit more capacity to an existing lab, or to give you a standalone compact solution to meet your needs.

Name: CXA_Grapple
Title: Grapple Fixture
Description: Grapple fixture to allow various points to manipulate station parts for assembly. Can also be used as a tiny docking port. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: CXA_Grapple_Standoff
Title: Grapple Fixture Standoff
Description: A small structural standoff to get a grapple fixture away from it's attached structure. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: CXA_GymHab
Title: eX-R-S Activity Module
Description: |2M Series Habitation Module| Keep your crew in shape with cardio and resistance excercises. Complete with a television to help pass time while burning off the snacks from your bingefest. Fitness module complete with shower and lavatory for personal hygiene and relief. Toilet paper and shampoo not included.

Name: CXA_KHM_Endcap
Title: Kerbal Habitation Module Endcap
Description: Give other cylidrical station modules a sleeker lookw ith these KHM Edcap Adapters.

Name: CXA_Kibo_Lab
Title: Joint Experiments Module (JEM)
Description: |2M Series Science Module| Thanks to extensive research and a higher development budget, a more efficient mobile procesing lab is now available. Module is equiped with a built-in battery bank and a large storage capacity. An integrated airlock is provided for transfering experiments between the lab and the outside environment, though some crew members have tested this cramped airlock for EVAs with some success.

Name: CXA_KU_ANTENNA
Title: KU-Band Communications Antenna
Description: This communications antenna has been specifically built for the purpose of downlinking high rate data from space stations. Dish is mounted to an extendable boom to clear adjacent station modules. This antenna also can act as a relay, with automatic store and forward capabilities as well as advanced pathfinding algorithms.

Name: CXA_MCBM
Title: Common Berthing Mechanism (Manual)
Description: 1.25m Common Berthing Mechanism intended to mate with passive counterparts. Ring variant specifically made for the Z1 truss component.

Name: CXA_NapHabV1
Title: Kerbal Habitation Module 3-1 (KHM-3-1)
Description: |2M Compact Series Habitation Module| Living space contains (3) bunks with associated personal storage lockers. Single point of entry to prevent use as a passageway. Hatch orientated in a manner to allow module to be used in a centrifuge.

Name: CXA_Node1
Title: Node-1 Utility Module
Description: |2M Series Habitation Module| Utility node with multiple docking location. Contains integral batteries and general stowage space.

Name: CXA_NodeCoverV1
Title: KHM-4-1 Node Cover
Description: |2M Compact Series Habitation Module| Structural node cover if you want to give you station a sleeker look. Compatible with Kerbal Habitation Module KHM-4-1.

Name: CXA_NodeCoverV2
Title: KHM-6-1 Node Cover
Description: |2M Compact Series Habitation Module| Structural node cover if you want to give you station a sleeker look. Compatible with Kerbal Habitation Module KHM-6-1.

Name: CXA_P5
Title: Solar Array Wing Spacer Truss (ITS)
Description: A rigid,lightweight truss segment developed as part of the Integrated Truss System (ITS). This truss section allows you to extend trusswork over deployed solar array wings. It is recommended to install truss segment using a robotic arm. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: CXA_P6_BATTERY_TRUSS
Title: Integrated Equipment Assembly Truss
Description: A rigid,lightweight truss segment developed as part of the Integrated Truss System (ITS). This truss includes integral electrical equipment such as batteries, battery chargers/dischargers, DC switching units, and DC-DC converters. Additionally this truss segment includes a pump flow control assembly for any thermal control system radiators which may be attached.

Name: CXA_P6_LONG_SPACER
Title: Long Spacer Truss (ITS)
Description: A rigid,lightweight truss segment developed as part of the Integrated Truss System (ITS).

Name: CXA_PCBM
Title: Common Berthing Mechanism (Passive)
Description: 1.25m Common Berthing Mechanism intended to mate with active counterparts.

Name: CXA_PMA
Title: Pressurized Mating Adapter
Description: Pressurized Mating Adapter [PMA] for mating of standard sized docking ports to 1.25M form factor docking ports.

Name: CXA_Quest_Airlock
Title: Quest Joint Airlock System
Description: |2M Series Airlock Module| The Quest Airlock provides a means for EVAs. Built with an "Equipment Lock" section for space suit and equipment storage, and a "Crew Lock" from which kerbalnauts can exit into space.

Name: CXA_RTAS_A
Title: RTAS(Active)
Description: The Rectangular Truss Attachment System (RTAS) was developed for allowing orbital construction of multiple truss segments. This specific variant is designed around the rectangular form factor Intergrated Truss System (ITS). Highly recommended to use a robotic arm for construction due to tight docking tolerances unless pilots are veterans at docking.

Name: CXA_RTAS_P
Title: RTAS(Passive)
Description: The Rectangular Truss Attachment System (RTAS) was developed for allowing orbital construction of multiple truss segments. This specific variant is designed around the rectangular form factor Intergrated Truss System (ITS). Highly recommended to use a robotic arm for construction due to tight docking tolerances unless pilots are veterans at docking.

Name: CXA_SAW
Title: Solar Array Wing(SAW)
Description: When normal solar panels can't cut it. The Solar Array Wing (SAW) contains 2 massive solar blankets that are deployed with the help of a collapsable mast (don't ask us how it works. Our best bet is black magic). Single-axis sun tracking functionality included.

Name: CXA_SleepHabV4-1
Title: Kerbal Habitation Module 4-1 (KHM-4-1)
Description: |2M Standard Series Habitation Module| Living space contains (4) bunks with associated personal storage lockers. Two points of entry at the ends, and three points of entry at the center, with one hatch oriented for module to be used in a centrifuge.

Name: CXA_SleepHabV4-2
Title: Kerbal Habitation Module 4-2 (KHM-4-2)
Description: |2M Standard Series Habitation Module| Living space contains (4) bunks with associated personal storage lockers. Two points of entry at the ends, and three points of entry at the center, with one hatch oriented for module to be used in a centrifuge. Too bad these are useless since the boys at the factory paneled over the hatches to make it look cleaner on the outside.

Name: CXA_SleepHabV6-1
Title: Kerbal Habitation Module 6-1 (KHM-6-1)
Description: |2M Standard Series Habitation Module| Living space contains (6) bunks with associated personal storage lockers. Three points of entry at the center, with one hatch oriented for module to be used in a centrifuge.

Name: CXA_SleepHabV6-2
Title: Kerbal Habitation Module 6-2 (KHM-6-2)
Description: |2M Standard Series Habitation Module| Living space contains (6) bunks with associated personal storage lockers. Three points of entry at the center, with one hatch oriented for module to be used in a centrifuge. Too bad the two side ones are useless since the boys at the factory paneled over the hatches to make it look cleaner on the outside.

Name: CXA_TRUNNION
Title: Trunnion Pin
Description: Mounting hardware for modules to be mounted within shuttle bays, or just to make crafts look cooler.

Name: CXA_Z1
Title: Z1 Truss
Description: The stepping stone truss that serves as a temporary mounting point for structural and pressurized assemblies on a station. Complete with integral reaction wheels to give a nudge without having to burn up RCS. Trus has been fitted with a built-in probe unit and a battery reserve.

Name: DB-605-A
Title: Daimler-Benz DB 605 A
Description: WWII-era V-12 liquid-cooled piston engine, the DB-605 A as produced by Daimler-Benz (GER). Used on the Messerschmitt Bf 109 fighter. 1475PS.

Name: DECOUPLER
Title: Soyuz FG/U/ST Truss Interstage Adapter
Description: A truss decoupler designed specifically to allow the "hot staging" of the R7 rocket. It combines a heatshield, avionics and a truss cage supporting the upper stage into a single part. This version is used on all modern variants of the Soyuz rocket.

Name: decoupler_ftr
Title: Heatshield Decoupler (Gray)
Description: Using a DRE heatshield just makes the bottom round, square it up with this decoupler that will fit nicely, flush, and hide the heatshield. Gray texture. TweakScale starting at 0.5m.

Name: decoupler_ftr_4m
Title: Heatshield Decoupler (Mk1-2)
Description: Special decoupler built especially for the Mk1-2 manned pod.

Name: decoupler_ftr_small
Title: Heatshield Decoupler (White)
Description: Using a DRE heatshield just makes the bottom round, square it up with this decoupler that will fit nicely, flush, and hide the heatshield. White texture. TweakScale starting at 0.5m.

Name: decoupler_ftr_smaller
Title: UP0625 Decoupler
Description: This decoupler is designed for use with the 0.625m heat shield. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0, RO IN PROGRESS)

Name: decoupler1-2
Title: Rockomax Brand Decoupler
Description: Rockomax is pleased to bring you the latest in decoupling technologies - twice the size of the next leading brand, Rockomax Brand Decouplers offer plenty of bang for plenty of buck! As with its smaller, woefully inferior competitor, the Rockomax Decoupler has handy arrows to indicate which side it will detach from.

Name: DecouplerDiamant
Title: Diamant Payload Decoupler
Description: A small decoupler for small payloads releasing.

Name: decouplersv05
Title: AIES SV-5 Base Decoupler
Description: Narrow version of Vector-B, probably fits only the AIES Engines. Base is installed first, engine should come in it, not the other way around. (PART NOT COSTED BY RP-0 BUT IN CORRECT NODE)

Name: decouplersvblack
Title: AIES SV-5 Black Base Decoupler
Description: Narrow version of Vector-B, probably fits only the AIES Engines. Base is installed first, engine should come in it, not vice versa. (PART NOT COSTED BY RP-0 BUT IN CORRECT NODE)

Name: DecouplerSylda
Title: Ariane 5 SYLDA Decoupler
Description: A stack decoupler for payloads releasing.

Name: DecouplerVega
Title: Vega Payload Decoupler
Description: A stack decoupler for payloads releasing.

Name: decoupvector
Title: AIES Vector-B Base Decoupler
Description: Will probably only fit the AIES Engines. Base is installed first, engine should come in it, not vice versa. (PART NOT COSTED BY RP-0 BUT IN CORRECT NODE)

Name: delta_small
Title: Small Delta Wing
Description: This small delta wing has breezed through extensive stress tests and design revisions, mostly because it wasn't involved in any of those. In any case, it should work as a comparatively reliable lifting surface.

Name: deltaWing
Title: Delta Wing
Description: Standard Delta configuration wings. These wings provide high lift and a stable center of gravity for your everyday lifting needs.

Name: desacopladorsat1
Title: AIES SAT-1 Decoupler
Description: Small decoupler for use in A1-RU5 Fairing Base. (PART NOT COSTED BY RP-0 BUT IN CORRECT NODE)

Name: desacopladorsat2
Title: AIES SAT-2 Decoupler
Description: Standard decoupler for use in V2-10R Fairing Base. (PART NOT COSTED BY RP-0 BUT IN CORRECT NODE)

Name: desacopladorsat3
Title: AIES SAT-3 Decoupler
Description: This ultra-thin decoupler is used to save the precious space so important in some crafts. (PART NOT COSTED BY RP-0 BUT IN CORRECT NODE)

Name: dest5Engine
Title: Generic 2kN Thruster
Description: Thruster for orbital maneuvers, similar to ones used in the Galileo probe. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: Diamant_Stage1
Title: Diamant A 1st stage "Emeraude"
Description: First stage of the Diamant A rocket, powered by an LRBA Vexin engine.

Name: Diamant_Stage2
Title: Diamant A/B 2nd stage "Topaze"
Description: The second stage of the Diamant rocket, and simultaneously the first stage of the Topaze sounding rocket. For complete realism add some small solid rockets at the top of this stage to spin stabilize the rocket before firing the third stage.

Name: Diamant_Stage3
Title: Diamant stage 3
Description: A small solid fuel booster.

Name: DiamantAsterix
Title: A-1 "Asterix"
Description: The first French satellite in orbit.

Name: DiamantFairing
Title: Diamant fairing
Description: A small fairing for a small satellite.

Name: dish_deploy_S
Title: CA-A10 Folding Dish Antenna
Description: The CA-A10 provides the advantages of a dish antenna without cluttering the front of your spacecraft. Electric servos fold the dish close to the hull during launch.

Name: dish_deploy_S2
Title: CA-AD1-R Folding Dish Antenna
Description: A medium gain directional antenna for short range, high bandwidth communications.

Name: dish_L
Title: Voyager 1 & 2 Parabolic Antenna
Description: The main parabolic telecommunications antenna of the Voyager spacecraft.

Name: dish_quetzal
Title: Pioneer 10 & 11 Parabolic Antenna
Description: The main parabolic telecommunications antenna of the Pioneer spacecraft.

Name: dish_S
Title: Ulysses Parabolic Antenna
Description: The main parabolic telecommunications antenna of the Ulysses spacecraft.

Name: dish_tatsujin
Title: MAVEN Parabolic Antenna
Description: The main parabolic telecommunications antenna of the the Mars Atmosphere and Volatile EvolutioN (MAVEN) spacecraft.

Name: Dishcl1
Title: AIES CommTech CL-1 Dish
Description: An early, small high-gain antenna. Rather wide cone and high bandwidth for Comm satellites in GEO, live video from the Moon, and similar tasks. Effective range ~37 Gm, power consumption 50 Watts.

Name: dishcomlar1
Title: AIES Comlar 1 Dish
Description: A powerful high-gain fixed dish, capable of reaching Saturn. High bandwidth.

Name: Dishmccomu
Title: AIES CommTech CM-60 Dish
Description: Medium dish, useful anywhere within the inner planets. Higher bandwidth than CL-1.

Name: Dishomega2g
Title: AIES CommTech Omega-2G Dish
Description: Excellent as an orbital relay, or for communicating as far as Jupiter.

Name: Dishpcf
Title: AIES CommTech PCF-5 Dish
Description: A light dish for short range communication. (PART IN PROGRESS, MAY NOT WORK)

Name: dm_antenna
Title: DM Upgrade
Description: DM Upgrade (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: dmAnomScanner
Title: Anomalous Signal Sensor - BTDT
Description: This small sensor is designed to scan for anomalous signals across several regions of the electromagnetic spectrum. You must be within 250m of the signal to obtain science results; use it from further out to obtain an estimate of the range and distance to the signal. For the best results, return the device to the KSC for further study. Can also interface with SCANsat equipment to function as a Been There Done That scanner.

Name: dmASERT
Title: Asteroid Sounding Experiment by Radiowave Transmission
Description: The ASERT is an asteroid-only experiment used to study the interior composition of asteroids. It must be paired with a second module placed on the opposite side of an asteroid. When two modules are properly positioned the experiment can be conducted with the science amount dependent on how much of the asteroid the signal passed through. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: dmBathymetry
Title: Submersible Oceanography and Bathymetry
Description: Use this submersible science package to explore the uncharted depths of the oceans. Data can be collected above and below the depth threshold to maximize science gain. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: dmbioDrill
Title: ExoKerbol Core Drill
Description: The ExoKerbol Core Drill (XKCD) is designed to collect subsurface core samples to search for signs of biological activity on atmospheric planets. Three drill core samples can be stored in the incubation chambers for return. Check drill animator orientation with the preview in the VAB/SPH.

Name: dmDAN
Title: Dynamic Albedo of Neutrons
Description: The Dynamic Albedo of Neutrons instrument scans the upper layers of the surface to detect any hydrogen molecules within, specifically searching for water.

Name: dmGoreSat
Title: Infrared Radiometer
Description: A cavity radiometer designed to measure the reflected and emitted infrared energy of a planetary body and to evaluate the albedo of the surface or cloud layers.

Name: dmImagingPlatform
Title: Multi-Spectral Imaging Platform
Description: This multi-spectral imaging platform is used to study the surface and composition of planets. Use only in orbit. Can also interface with SCANsat equipment to function as a biome scanner and as a minerals detector.

Name: dmmagBoom
Title: Magnetometer Boom
Description: The magnetometer instruments are used to determine the magnitude and direction of planetary magnetic fields. The long boom separates these instruments from any interference caused by magnetic elements in the probe. Use in low to high orbit or on the surface. Not for use during atmospheric flight. Can also interface with SCANsat equipment to function as an ore scanner.

Name: dmReconLarge
Title: Big Brother Stereo Surveillance Camera
Description: This advanced surveillance camera features two telescopes designed to capture stereographic images while sweeping 90 degree bands of the surface. It includes four non-reusable film cannisters and has extensive on-board processing capabilities. Use this when only the best spy photos of the surface will suffice. Can be used at up to five times the normal low orbit altitude. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: dmReconSmall
Title: Little Brother Surveillance Camera
Description: This single-camera surveillance telescope features a continuously panning aperture that covers 110 degree bands of the surface. This model features two non-reusable film cannisters and has limited on-board processing capabilities. Use for obtaining detailed photos of the surface or spotting any unusual features. Can be used at up to five times the normal low orbit altitude. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: dmRoverGoo
Title: Micro Goo Containment Pod
Description: Advances in materials science have allowed for the construction of a tiny goo pod capable of storing two independent samples simultaneously. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: dmRoverMat
Title: SC-901 Science Micro
Description: New construction techniques have allowed the standard SC-9001 to be built in a new, compact enclosure capable of storing two samples simultaneously. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: dmscope
Title: Orbital Telescope
Description: This telescope makes things that are far away look like they are less far away. Use in low to high orbits. Not for use during atmospheric flight or on the surface.

Name: dmSeismicHammer
Title: Seismic Impact Hammer
Description: The Seismic Impact Hammer is used to generate seismic waves that provide information about a planet's interior. Use in conjunction with one or more Seismic Sensor Pods to maximize science return. The hammer must impact the surface for the experiment to succeed. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: dmSeismicPod
Title: Seismic Sensor Pod
Description: The Seismic Sensor Pod is designed to be used in conjunction with the DMagic Seismic Impact Hammer. Place at least two pods at variable distances away from the impact hammer using the built-in decoupler mechanism (the pod has a very high impact tolerance) or by placing them on a separate vessel. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: dmSIGINT
Title: Oversize Signals Intelligence Satellite
Description: A grossly oversized radio signals intelligence dish that can be used for listening in to every imaginable from of communication, discovering radio anomalies on a planet's surface, or just impressing your neighbor. Warning: Dish is FRAGILE; it is NOT for use in the atmosphere; CANNOT be retracted! Can be used at up to five times the normal low orbit altitude. This instrument can also be used as a powerful communications antenna. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: dmSIGINT_End
Title: Oversize Signals Intelligence Satellite
Description: A grossly oversized radio signals intelligence dish that can be used for listening in to every imaginable from of communication, discovering radio anomalies on a planet's surface, or just impressing your neighbor. This instrument also servers as a nose cone, and uses deployable fairing shrouds. Warning: Dish is FRAGILE; it is NOT for use in the atmosphere; CANNOT be retracted! Can be used at up to five times the normal low orbit altitude. This instrument can also be used as a powerful communications antenna. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: dmSIGINT_Small
Title: Undersize Signals Intelligence Satellite
Description: A mildly oversized radio signals intelligence dish that can be used for listening in to every imaginable from of communication, discovering radio anomalies on a planet's surface, or just impressing your neighbor. Warning: Dish is FRAGILE; it is NOT for use in the atmosphere; CANNOT be retracted! Can be used at up to five times the normal low orbit altitude. This instrument can also be used as a powerful communications antenna. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: dmSoilMoisture
Title: Soil Moisture Sensor
Description: This orbital sensor deploys a large L-band microwave detector comprised of 82 individual antenna elements. It can be used to study the water content of the upper soil layers and the salinity levels of large water features. Can only be used in low orbit. This instrument can also be used as a powerful communications antenna. Can also interface with SCANsat equipment to function as a water scanner.
PLACEMENT NOTES: On the SMOS, SMAP and SAC-D Satellites

Name: dmSolarCollector
Title: Solar Particle Collector
Description: This instrument is designed to collect and store several samples of solar particles.

Name: dmsurfacelaser
Title: Surface Ablation Laser Light Imager
Description: Presenting the latest in laser based geological science. This device is capable of vaporizing surface samples to study their composition and expose hidden layers of the surface for further study. Warning: DMagic Orbital Science does not condone the use of this laser in any space combat related hijinks, please refrain from such activities.

Name: dmUSAccGrav
Title: Univ. Storage - Accelerometer / Gravmax
Description: Combines the Double-C Seismic Accelerometer and Gravmax Negative Gravioli Detector into one convenient and aerodynamic container. Use with New Horizon's Universal Storage system.

Name: dmUSAsert
Title: Univ. Storage - ASERT
Description: The ASERT is an asteroid-only experiment used to study the interior composition of asteroids. It must be paired with a second module placed on the opposite side of an asteroid. When two modules are properly positioned the experiment can be conducted with the science amount dependent on how much of the asteroid the signal passed through. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: dmUSAtmosSense
Title: Univ. Storage - Atmospheric Sensor
Description: The latest in R&D enabled the development of this little marvel, The Sensor Array Computing Nose Cone. It is outfitted with many "quality" sensors and a computer salvaged from the highest quality aircraft scrap, enabling it to collect atmospheric data while in flight.

Name: dmUSGoo
Title: Biological Sample Capsule
Description: This is a capsule containing biological samples (fruit flies, fungus, perhaps even a mouse or two). While some observations of the sample may be transmitted, only by recovering the sample safely can the most information be gained about life's response to the given situation.

Name: dmUSGoreSat
Title: Univ. Storage - GORESat
Description: The Global Orbital Radiance Experiment Satellite (GORESat) monitors the total light reflected from a planet's surface across multiple wavelengths using four cavity radiometers. Can only be used from high orbit.

Name: dmUSImagingPlatform
Title: Univ. Storage - Multi-Spectral Imaging Platform
Description: This multi-spectral imaging platform is used to study the surface and composition of planets. Use only in orbit. Can also interface with SCANsat equipment to function as a biome scanner and as a minerals detector.

Name: dmUSMagBoom
Title: Univ. Storage - Magnetometer Boom
Description: The magnetometer instruments are used to determine the magnitude and direction of planetary magnetic fields. The long boom separates these instruments from any interference caused by magnetic elements in the probe. Use in low to high orbit or on the surface. Not for use during atmospheric flight. Use with New Horizon's Universal Storage system. Can also interface with SCANsat equipment to function as an ore scanner.

Name: dmUSMat
Title: Univ. Storage - SC-9001 Science Jr.
Description: The US-SC-9001 is a cutting edge, self contained laboratory. Have you ever wondered what happens to something in zero G? Or, have you ever pondered the truly meaningful questions? Such as what would happen if I exposed this to the rigors of stellar radiation and an unforgiving vacuum? Comes with complimentary notepad. Recommended for ages 4-8. Small parts inside make it not suitable for small children.

Name: dmUSPresTemp
Title: Univ. Storage - PresMat / 2Hot / X-Ray
Description: Combines a barometer, temperature sensor, and geiger counter into a single convenient container. Use with New Horizon's Universal Storage System.

Name: dmUSScope
Title: Univ. Storage - Orbital Telescope
Description: This telescope makes things that are far away look like they are less far away. Use in low to high orbits. Not for use during atmospheric flight or on the surface.

Name: dmUSSoilMoisture
Title: Univ. Storage - Soil Moisture Sensor
Description: This orbital sensor deploys a large L-band microwave detector comprised of 82 individual antenna elements. It can be used to study the water content of the upper soil layers and the salinity levels of large water features. Can only be used in low orbit. This instrument can also be used as a powerful communications antenna. Can also interface with SCANsat equipment to function as a water scanner.
PLACEMENT NOTES: On the SMOS, SMAP and SAC-D Satellites
COST NOTES: Slightly more than the regular part because there is miniaturization and additional parts

Name: dmUSSolarParticles
Title: Univ. Storage - Solar Particle Collector
Description: This instrument is designed to collect and store several samples of solar particles.

Name: dmXRay
Title: XRF Spectrometer
Description: This instrument collects a small surface sample and determines its exact mineral composition through X-Ray fluorescence.

Name: docking-25
Title: Manual Berthing Mechanism
Description: In an effort to allow girders and the such to attach to a Common Berthing Mechanism port Boeing created the manually operated Manual Berthing Mechanism (MBM).

Name: dockingPort1
Title: NASA Docking System (Shielded)
Description: This is the stock shielded docking port sized to the new NASA Docking System.

Name: dockingPort2
Title: NASA Docking System
Description: This is the stock docking port sized to the new NASA Docking System.

Name: dockingPort3
Title: Docking Port (propellant only)
Description: This small docking port does not have a tube for personnel transfers; at best propellant can be routed through it, but its real purpose is to train crew in docking procedures.

Name: dockingPortLarge
Title: Common Berthing Mechanism
Description: The Common Berthing Mechanism.

Name: dockingPortLateral
Title: NASA Docking System
Description: The new NASA Docking System.

Name: Draco
Title: Draco
Description: The Draco thruster is a small rocket engine for use on the Dragon spacecraft. The Draco's thrust is comparable to the Marquardt R-4D engine developed for the Apollo Service and Lunar Modules in 1960s. The Draco thruster is used for apogee/perigee maneuvers, orbit adjustment, and attitude control. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: DUNARETROTANK
Title: RL - I Propellant Tank
Description: A generic pressurized propellant tank for surface habitation modules.

Name: EAS
Title: Soyuz Launch Escape System Abort Motor
Description: The Launch Escape System abort motor assembly for the Soyuz TM/TMA/MS spacecraft. It contains a powerful solid rocket motor with two sets of nozzles, providing very high thrust needed to separate the Orbital and Descent modules from the rocket. Unlike older variants, it fires long enough to allow the main parachute to be deployed. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: EAS_top
Title: Soyuz Launch Escape System Jettison Motor
Description: A small, multi-nozzle solid motor designed to cleanly separate the Soyuz launch escape system assembly from the fairing during a nominal flight. It can also pull away the entire upper section of the fairing in case of an abort. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: EjectionCover2A
Title: EjectionCover2A
Description: Seat Ejection Module.  Add this module to any command pod enable the crew pilot ejection feature for up to 3 crew members FROM THAT POD.  Parachute will auto-deploy once it is safe to do so.  Crew will be ejected from the nearest available, unobstructed hatch.  You can add multiple modules for more ejection seats. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: EjectionModule
Title: EjectionModule
Description: Seat Ejection Module.  Add this module to any command pod enable the crew pilot ejection feature for a single crew member FROM THAT POD.  Parachute will auto-deploy once it is safe to do so.  Crew will be ejected from the nearest available, unobstructed hatch.  You can add multiple modules for more ejection seats. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: elevon2
Title: Elevon 2
Description: Made from the finest materials at hand, these flight surfaces are guaranteed to operate while attached to the craft. However studies have shown that a lack of atmosphere *may* slightly impede function. No refunds.

Name: elevon3
Title: Elevon 3
Description: Made from the finest materials at hand, these flight surfaces are guaranteed to operate while attached to the craft. However studies have shown that a lack of atmosphere *may* slightly impede function. No refunds.

Name: elevon5
Title: Elevon 5
Description: Just another one of these elevon things... wait, this one is swept! Wow!

Name: engine-pod-1
Title: SD-01 Radial Engine Pod
Description: It was discovered through focus group testing that many space programs like their radially attached engines to "look cool" and give an appearance of speed. Hence, Rockomax devised the SD series of engine pods, which, let's be frank, are mostly for looks. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: engine-pod-2
Title: SD-02 Radial Engine Pod
Description: Housing two engine attach points this time. The Rockomax engineers have really outdone themselves. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: engineexper05
Title: RL60 Vacuum Engine
Description: Next generation cryogenic upper stage engine designed to replace the RL10, providing higher performance while maintaining the same installation envelope.  Also available in a lower 180kN thrust Vinci-180 model. Diameter: [1.5 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: engineLargeSkipper
Title: RL10 Series Vacuum Engine
Description: Hydrolox restartable expander-cycle vacuum engine used in multiple upper stages, including Centaur, the Saturn I S-IV, and the Delta Cryogenic Second Stage. It has low thrust, but very high specific impulse and low mass, making it ideal for high energy, beyond-low-Earth-orbit applications like launching satellites to geostationary transfer orbits or to the Moon or other planets. However, like all hydrolox engines, hydrogen boiloff is a serious issue without heat pumps or radiators. Diameter: [0.92 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: engineLargeSkipper_125m
Title: Merlin Series
Description: The whole family of Merlin rocket engines, made by SpaceX. Diameter: [1.75 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: enginelmodc
Title: Lunar Module Descent Engine
Description: Deeply throttleable pressure-fed vacuum engine used for the descent module of the Apollo lunar lander. Uses storable propellants which are not subject to boiloff, but are far less efficient than hydrolox or even kerolox. The version used on J-class missions had slightly higher specific impulse (this, along with other changes, gave enough payload capacity for the rover, for example). A later variant (TR-201) was used on Delta as an upper stage engine (on Delta P series); this was a low-cost model with more restarts (4 instead of 2) and slightly higher thrust but lower efficiency and no throttling capability. Diameter: [1.5 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: eos_aqua
Title: Aqua
Description: Earth Observing System satellite Aqua

Name: eos_aura
Title: Aura
Description: Earth Observing System satellite Aura

Name: eos_tdrs
Title: Tracking and Data Relay Satellite H-N
Description: Earth Observing System TDRS-H/I/J/K/L/M/N Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: eos_terra
Title: Terra
Description: Earth Observing System satellite Terra

Name: eos_terraalt
Title: Terra Side Solar Panel
Description: Side solar panel for Terra satellite

Name: escalerar2s
Title: AIES ESCALER R2S Mobility Enhancer
Description: Compact ladder, should be positioned without anything blocking it from below so it could be extended downwards twice in size.

Name: expendLandingLeg
Title: AIES 'Expend' Landing
Description: Small leg, just right for your lightweight probes.

Name: explonpod
Title: AS-4000 Satellite Bus
Description: Satellite bus as used in the GPS IIF Satellites.

Name: explorer_6
Title: Explorer 6
Description: Explorer probe 6

Name: ExSmallGearBay
Title: Gemini Extra Small Gear Bay
Description: High performance tiny gear designed for atmospheric use.

Name: ExtCamRadialVErt
Title: External Radial-mount Camera (vertical)
Description: Additional Camera (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: F8f?Bearcat?Cockpit
Title: F8F Bearcat Cockpit
Description: Vroom vroom vroom ^_^ (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: fairing1
Title: Skylab Fairing 1
Description: This is the first of four fairings for Skylab. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: fairing3
Title: Skylab Fairing 2-4
Description: This is the second,third and fourth of four fairings for Skylab. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: fairingSize1
Title: FB - FF1 Airstream Protective Shell
Description: While the Kerbals at Mission Control were still figuring out how to get their rockets back down to Kerbin safely, the research engineers at FLOOYD were quickly realising that protecting parts on ascent was just as important. Heavy research into two-dimensional-input driven procedural construction was then funded with the hopes of making protective shells for important payloads and interstage areas of the crafts. The protective shells also have the benefit of making the craft more aerodynamic, hopefully saving on precious rocket fuel! The AE-FF1 is the smallest size available from FLOOYD.

Name: fairingSize2
Title: FB - FF2 Airstream Protective Shell
Description: While the Kerbals at Mission Control were still figuring out how to get their rockets back down to Kerbin safely, the research engineers at FLOOYD were quickly realising that protecting parts on ascent was just as important. Heavy research into two-dimensional-input driven procedural construction was then funded with the hopes of making protective shells for important payloads and interstage areas of the crafts. The protective shells also have the benefit of making the craft more aerodynamic, hopefully saving on precious rocket fuel! The AE-FF2 is the mid-range size available from FLOOYD.

Name: fairingSize3
Title: FB - FF3 Airstream Protective Shell
Description: While the Kerbals at Mission Control were still figuring out how to get their rockets back down to Kerbin safely, the research engineers at FLOOYD were quickly realising that protecting parts on ascent was just as important. Heavy research into two-dimensional-input driven procedural construction was then funded with the hopes of making protective shells for important payloads and interstage areas of the crafts. The protective shells also have the benefit of making the craft more aerodynamic, hopefully saving on precious rocket fuel! The AE-FF3 is the largest size available from FLOOYD.

Name: FASA_Apollo_Float_Ring
Title: Float Rings 2.5m
Description: Water floats for your 2.5m Command Module. Place in 4x symmetry and deploy just after splashdown.

Name: FASA_Apollo_Float_Ring125
Title: Float Rings 1.25m
Description: Water floats for your 1.25m Command Module. Place in 4x symmetry and deploy just after splashdown. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: FASA_Apollo_Float_Round
Title: Float Spheres
Description: Floats spheres for water landings. They have a high heat resistance and impact rating for use as aero breaks and airbags.

Name: FASA_Apollo_Float_RoundXL
Title: Float Spheres XL
Description: Extra large floats spheres for water landings. They have a high heat resistance and impact rating for use as aero breaks and airbags. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: FASA_Atlas_LFT_Cone
Title: Mercury - Atlas Launch Vehicle Fuel Tank
Description: The fuel tank for the Mercury - Atlas Launch Vehicle, aka Atlas D Mercury Launch Vehicle, aka Atlas LV-3B.

Name: FASA_Atlas_LFT_Cone2
Title: Atlas-E/F Fuel Tank
Description: The fuel tank for the Atlas-E/F series.

Name: FASA_BigGeminiParachute2
Title: Big Gemini Recovery Main Parachute
Description: The Big Gemini parachute. Put this on top of the RCS Control section when making Big Gemini (instead of the regular Gemini parachute).

Name: FASA_Gemini_ASAS_Comp
Title: Remote Control Unit
Description: Add to a spacecraft to add autonomous operation for testing without risking the life of a Kerbal.

Name: FASA_Gemini_Lander_Eng
Title: FASA Advanced Gemini Lander Engine
Description: The main engine for the Gemini Lander. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASA_Gemini_Lander_Leg_Part
Title: FASA Advanced Gemini Lander Leg
Description: Lander leg for the Gemini one man lander.

Name: FASA_Gemini_Lander_Legs
Title: Gemini Lander Legs
Description: Lander legs for the Gemini one man lander

Name: FASA_Gemini_Lander_LFT
Title: FASA Advanced Gemini Lander LFT
Description: The liquid fuel tanks from the lander as its own part for custom creations. Use with the Gemini Lander Engine.

Name: FASA_Gemini_Lander_Pod
Title: Gemini Lightweight Lander
Description: Gemini Lander Pod. Contains one astronaut.

Name: FASA_Gemini_RCS_Thrusters
Title: Gemini RCS Thruster Pack
Description: Gemini thrusters go on the bottom of your Gemini adapter equipment section. They only thrust laterally, Left and Right. RCS O/F Ratio 1.3:1.

Name: FASA_Mercury_Eng
Title: Mercury Retro Rocket Pack
Description: This pack contains 3 solid rocket engines to de-orbit the Mercury capsule. They are each 1000lbf (4.448kN) and burn for 10 seconds and are fired at five second intervals, thus peak thrust is 8.9kN). Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASA_Mercury_LES
Title: Mercury Launch Escape System
Description: Set up an action group to turn on the engine. Otherwise staging will just release it. Attach this to the top of your Mercury capsule, in case there is an emergency. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASA_Mercury_LFEng
Title: Storable Propellant Retro Pack (2kN class)
Description: This is the equivalent in thrust of two Generic 1kN thrusters. Pressure-fed from bladder tanks, effectively infinite ignitions and no ullage issues. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASA_Mercury_LFT_Long
Title: Mercury - Redstone LV Fuel Tank
Description: The fuel tank for the Mercury - Redstone Launch Vehicle. Used for sub-orbital flights.

Name: FASA_Mercury_LFT_Short
Title: FASA Fuel Tank
Description: A generic fuel tank.

Name: FASA_Mercury_Parachute_Box
Title: Mercury Parachute
Description: The Mercury recovery parachute. Sits on the capsule with the nose fairing on top of it.

Name: FASA_Mercury_RCS_Short
Title: FASA Pressurized Fuel Tank
Description: A generic pressurized fuel tank.

Name: FASA_Mercury_Redstone_Eng
Title: NAA-75-110 A-Series
Description: Used on the Redstone missile.  Designed for Ethanol/LOx (A-6) (1.5 O/F Ratio), it was later adapted to burn Hydyne/LOx (A-7) (1.73 O/F Ratio)(higher performance (12%) yet more toxic) for use in Jupiter C / Juno I.  When Redstone MRLV was adapted from Jupiter C for manned use the A7 was switched back to Ethanol, accepting slightly lower performance for lack of toxicity. Thrust Vector Control was provided by carbon thrust vanes (add the Redstone Fin / Thrust vane part in 4x symmetry), and additional attitude control was provided by actuating fins. Mass includes thrust frame. Diameter: [1.77 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASA_RO_UA1207
Title: UA1207 SRM
Description: Strap-on booster for Titan 3M. Burn time 117s. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASA_RO_UA1563
Title: UA1563 SRM
Description: Strap-on booster for uprated Titan 3 and Saturn INT / MLV applications.  Burn time 101s or 157s, depending on configuration chosen Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASA_RO_UA1564
Title: UA1564 SRM
Description: Strap-on booster for uprated Titan 3 and Saturn INT / MLV applications.  Burn time 101s or 157s, depending on configuration chosen Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASA_SIB
Title: Saturn S-IB Stage
Description: This part is the fuel/oxidizer tanks and thrust structure for the S-IB found on the Saturn IB. Attach 8 Rocketdyne H-1 engines and 8 fins to the bottom of the stage.

Name: FASAAgena_Engine
Title: XLR81 (Agena) Vacuum Engine
Description: Gas-generator nitric acid/UDMH vacuum engine used on Agena. The XLR81 family was derived from the Bell Hustler Rocket Engine, which was developed for use on an air-to-surface missile. Early engines were nearly identical to the Hustler engine, while later variants offered new capabilities and improved performance. Engine restart was introduced on the Agena B's XLR81-BA-7 (Model 8081). The XLR81-BA-11 (Model 8096) used on Agena D used propellant sumps to eliminate the need for ullage thrust. The XLR81-BA-13 (Model 8247) powered the Gemini Agena Target Vehicle (a modified Agena D) and was rated for up to 14 restarts. Diameter: [0.9 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAAgena_Engine_FP
Title: Agena-D Flight Pack with SPS
Description: Flight Pack (RCS, SPS) for Agena-D and BAC Model 8096/8247 engine. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAAgena_Engine_FP_b
Title: Agena-B Flight Pack
Description: Flight Pack RCS for Agena-B and BAC Model 8081 engine.

Name: FASAAgena_Engine_FP_d
Title: Agena-D Flight Pack
Description: Flight Pack RCS (with no SPS) for Agena-D and BAC Model 8096/8247 engine.

Name: FASAAgenaAnt
Title: Agena-D Antenna
Description: An extendible antenna for the Agena-D.

Name: FASAAgenaDocking
Title: Gemini Agena Target/Docking Adapter
Description: Gemini target/docking adapter used to convert an Agena-D into a Gemini Agena Target Vehicle. Better put a fairing on it too.

Name: FASAAgenaLFT
Title: Agena-D Propellant Tank
Description: Propellant tanks for the Agena-D.

Name: FASAAgenaLFT_b
Title: Agena-B Propellant Tank
Description: Propellant tanks for the Agena-B.

Name: FASAAgenaProbe
Title: Agena Bus/Guidance Unit
Description: The Agena electronics and avionics package. Provides an 11.8 kWh battery, providing control for just over 47 hr, and an omnidirectional antenna with an effective range of 1,500 km to ground stations.

Name: FASAALSEP_Device
Title: Passive Seismic Experiment Package (PSEP)
Description: Self supporting equipment to measure moonquakes in a passive manner. Requires KAS plugin to be deployed.

Name: FASAALSEP_Reflector
Title: Laser Ranging Retroreflector (LRRR)
Description: Lunar Laser Ranging Experiment. A specialized retroreflector for allowing distance measurement from the Earth to the Moon. Requires KAS plugin to be deployed.

Name: FASAALSEP_Scanner
Title: Apollo Lunar Module ALSEP Scanner
Description: SURFACE ONLY. Apollo science. Conduct your experiment while unit is still attached on lander. Requires KAS plugin to be deployed.

Name: FASAApalloLFTF1Plate
Title: Saturn C-8 Second Stage
Description: The second stage for the Saturn C-8 launch vehicle.  Attach 8 J-2 engines.

Name: FASAApalloLFTJ2
Title: Saturn Fuel Tank
Description: A fuel tank with Saturn type markings.

Name: FASAApalloLFTJ25XPlate
Title: Saturn S-II Stage
Description: The S-II stage as found on the Saturn V. Attach 5 Rocketdyne J-2 engines and the aft interstage to the bottom.

Name: FASAApalloLFTJ2Nova
Title: Saturn C-8 First Stage
Description: An extremely large liquid fuel tank for the first stage of the Saturn C-8 launch vehicle. 50ft Diameter.  Attach 8 F-1 engines.

Name: FASAApalloLFTJ2Plate
Title: Saturn S-IVB Stage
Description: The S-IVB stage as found on the Saturn series. The Rocketdyne J-2 Rocket Engine and aft interstage attach to this part.

Name: FASAApalloLFTS1BStage1
Title: Saturn S-IB Stage Tanks
Description: This is the fuel/oxidizer tanks assembly for the S-IB found on the Saturn IB.

Name: FASAApalloLFTSVS1
Title: Saturn S-IC Stage
Description: The S-IC stage as found on the Saturn V. Attach 5 Rocketdyne F-1 engines and 4 fairings to the bottom of the stage.

Name: FASAApalloLFTSVS2
Title: Saturn Fuel Tank
Description: A fuel tank with Saturn type markings.

Name: FASAApollo_CM
Title: Apollo Command Module
Description: Apollo Command Module. Contains three astronauts.

Name: FASAApollo_CM_Decoupler
Title: Apollo Command/Service Module Decoupler
Description: This part separates the Command Module from the Service Module.

Name: FASAApollo_CM_HeatShield
Title: Apollo Command Module Heat Shield
Description: This part is the ablative heat shield for the Apollo Command Module.

Name: FASAApollo_CM_parachutes
Title: Apollo Command Module Main Parachutes
Description: The three main recovery parachutes for the Apollo Command Module.

Name: FASAApollo_CM_Top
Title: Apollo Command Module Forward Heat Shield
Description: This heat shield protects the earth landing (recovery) system components and everything else in the forward compartment.

Name: FASAApollo_DockingDevice
Title: Apollo Docking Mechanism Probe
Description: Apollo Command Module Docking Probe. Will only work with the Apollo Lunar Module Drogue.

Name: FASAApollo_LES
Title: Apollo Launch Escape System
Description: The LEA provides the means for separation the CM from the launch vehicle during pad or suborbital aborts. This assembly consists of a Q-ball instrumentation assembly, ballast compartment, canard surfaces, pitch control motor, tower jettison motor, launch escape motor, a structural skirt, an open-frame tower, and a boost protective cover.

Name: FASAApollo_SM
Title: Apollo Service Module with RCS
Description: The Apollo Service Module. Contains fuel, RCS, ECS, fuel cell, and batteries. This has RCS pods built in.

Name: FASAApollo_SM_Dish
Title: Apollo Service Module High Gain Antenna
Description: The steerable unified S-band high-gain antenna for communication between Earth, the CSM, and the LM.

Name: FASAApollo_SM_Engine
Title: AJ10-137 (Service Propulsion System)
Description: The Aerojet AJ10-137 rocket engine used on the Apollo Service Module as the Service Propulsion System. Diameter: [3.9 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAApollo_SM_Light
Title: Apollo Service Module Docking Light
Description: An extending light to provide some illumination for critical manoeuvres.

Name: FASAApollo_SM_RCS
Title: Apollo Service Module RCS Quad Pod
Description: This is the RCS Quad Pods for the Apollo Service Module. Each contains it's own pressurization and fuel. Place 4 pods 90 degrees apart. 2:1 O/F Ratio.

Name: FASAApollo_SubSatAnt
Title: Apollo Sub-Satellite Antenna
Description: Antenna for the Pioneer probe. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: FASAApolloAPS
Title: Saturn IB/V - APS Flight Pack
Description: This unique engine/RCS combo even comes with a little bit of fuel. Great for probes and control motors. RCS O/F Ratio 1.63:1. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAApolloDecSV5m
Title: Saturn S-II Aft Interstage - Bottom
Description: This part is the bottom part of the Saturn S-II stage aft interstage aboard the Saturn V launch vehicle.

Name: FASAApolloIU
Title: Saturn IB/V Instrument Unit
Description: The Saturn Instrument Unit provides command and control for the final stages of the Saturn IB/V series vehicles. Could be used with any other 260" launch vehicles.

Name: FASAApolloLFEF1
Title: F-1 Series
Description: The massive Rocketdyne F-1 engine. One of the largest, most powerful rocket engines ever built. Ensure you enable roll capability or disable gimbal as required for your application. Diameter: [3.61 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAApolloLFEH1
Title: H-1/RS-27 Series
Description: The H-1 is an upgrade to the LR79 engine that propelled the Saturn-I and IB vehicles, as well as late-model Delta rockets (as the RS-27). The H-1/RS-27 are optimized for the first-stage main engine role. The RS-27A has a higher expansion ratio for increased performance at altitude since liftoff thrust on the Delta II is augmented by solid boosters and the core burns rather longer. Diameter: [1.0 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAApolloLFEJ2
Title: J-2 Series
Description: The Rocketdyne J-2 rocket engine found on the Saturn S-IVB and S-II stages. Ensure you enable roll capability or disable gimbal as required for your application. Diameter: [2.01 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAApolloLFEM1
Title: M-1 Series
Description: The massive M-1 engine. The largest, most powerful, LH2/LOX engine ever designed. Individual components have been tested. Generally designed as an upper stage engine, first stages designs with expanding nozzles were being worked on. Diameter: [4.28 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAApolloLFERL10
Title: RL10 Series Vacuum Engine
Description: Hydrolox restartable expander-cycle vacuum engine used in multiple upper stages, including Centaur, the Saturn I S-IV, and the Delta Cryogenic Second Stage. It has low thrust, but very high specific impulse and low mass, making it ideal for high energy, beyond-low-Earth-orbit applications like launching satellites to geostationary transfer orbits or to the Moon or other planets. However, like all hydrolox engines, hydrogen boiloff is a serious issue without heat pumps or radiators. Diameter: [0.92 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAApolloStrJ2Fairing
Title: Saturn S-IVB Stage Aft Interstage
Description: This part is the aft interstage for the S-IVB aboard the Saturn S-IB Launch Vehicle.

Name: FASAApolloStrJ2StrJ23m5mDec
Title: Saturn S-IVB Stage Aft Interstage
Description: This part is the aft interstage for the S-IVB when used with the Saturn V.

Name: FASAApolloStrJ2StrJ23m5mDecNova
Title: Saturn C-8 Interstage
Description: An interstage separating the first and second stage of the Saturn C-8 launch vehicle. 33ft to 50ft Diameter.

Name: FASAApolloStrJ2StrJ25mDec
Title: Saturn S-II Aft Interstage - Top
Description: This part is the top part of the Saturn S-II stage aft interstage aboard the Saturn V launch vehicle.

Name: FASAApolloStrS1BPlate
Title: Engine Mount
Description: Engine mounting part for multiple engines.

Name: FASAApolloStrS1BPlateNova
Title: Engine Mount
Description: Engine mounting part for multiple engines.

Name: FASAApolloSubSat
Title: Apollo Sub-Satellite
Description: The Apollo Sub-Satellite is a mini deployable survey satellite for Apollo to provide information on a planet or moons natural resources. Also has its own solar power. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: FASAAtlasH
Title: Atlas G/H/I Fuel Tank
Description: The fuel tank for the Atlas G/H/I. Historically used with the Centaur D1A to send up to 2.375T to GTO.

Name: FASAAtlasII
Title: Atlas II Fuel Tank
Description: The fuel tank for the Atlas II. Historically used with the Centaur D2 to send up to 3.8T to GTO.

Name: FASAAtlasLV3C
Title: Atlas LV-3C Fuel Tank
Description: The fuel tank for the Atlas LV-3C. Historically used to loft the Centaur D1 into orbit, but has many uses.

Name: FASAAtlasSLV3A
Title: Atlas SLV-3A Fuel Tank
Description: The fuel tank for the Atlas SLV-3A launcher.  Extended fuel tank for larger payloads.

Name: FASAAtlasSLV3C
Title: Atlas SLV-3C/D Fuel Tank
Description: The fuel tank for the Atlas SLV-3C/D. Historically used with the Centaur D1 to send 1.75T (3C) or 1.80T (3D) to GTO.  Reduce fuel by 3t to setup the earlier 3C. (PART NOT COSTED BY RP-0 BUT IN CORRECT NODE)

Name: FASABigGeminiRetroModule
Title: Big Gemini Retro Module
Description: The Big Gemini Retro Module that contains 4x solid rockets to de-orbit Big Gemini. Decouples before re-entry.  Provides approximately 106dV for re-entry burn.

Name: FASADeltaAv0
Title: Thor Avionics Unit
Description: Small, 1.5m avionics unit for Thor and Thrust Augmented Thor rocket stage.  Used on Thor-Able, Thor-Agena, Thor-Ablestar, Thor-Burner, Thor-Delta and early Delta rockets (A-K).

Name: FASADeltaAv1
Title: Thor/Delta Avionics Unit
Description: Early 2.44m avionics unit for Long Tank Thor and Long Tank Thrust Augmented Thor rocket stage.  Delta L-N and Delta 0.

Name: FASADeltaAv2
Title: Delta Avionics Unit
Description: Avionics unit for the Extended Long Tank Thor and Extra Extended Long Tank Thor rocket stages. Delta I and Delta II.

Name: FASADeltaAv3
Title: DCSS-4 Avionics Unit
Description: Integrated avionics unit for 4m Delta Cryogenic Second Stage and Delta III/IV-M launch vehicle.

Name: FASADeltaAv4
Title: DCSS-5 Avionics Unit
Description: Integrated avionics unit for 5m Delta Cryogenic Second Stage and Delta IV-M/IV-HLV launch vehicle.

Name: FASADeltaCastorSrb
Title: Castor 1 Solid Rocket Motor
Description: A booster motor for the Delta D rocket. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASADeltaConeLFT
Title: Delta Cone Rocket Fuel Tank
Description: A cone shaped rocket fuel tank for the Delta rocket. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: FASADeltaMB3LFE
Title: LR79 Series
Description: Long-lasting US Kerolox gas-generator booster engine. The same components and broadly the same performance as the LR89, the LR79 (also known as S-3D in Jupiter / Juno II) powered Jupiter, Thor, and Thor-Delta (Delta) rockets. Diameter: [1.53 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAE1
Title: E-1
Description: Pump-fed kerolox open cycle (gas generator) booster engine developed from LR79/89. Backup proposal for the first stage engine on the Titan 1 ICBM, and proposed first stage engine on the Saturn 1 but ultimately never flown (4 E-1s replaced with 8 H-1s). Diameter: [2.14 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAExplorerLFTLong
Title: Juno I Tank
Description: A stretched Redstone tank for Jupiter-C / Juno I. Fill with LOX/Hydyne for use with NAA75-110 engine in LOX/Hydyne mode.

Name: FASAExplorerLFTMed
Title: FASA Fuel Tank
Description: A generic fuel tank.

Name: FASAExplorerLFTSmall
Title: FASA Fuel Tank
Description: A generic fuel tank.

Name: FASAExplorerNosecone
Title: Juno I Nosecone Fairing & Instrument Section
Description: Nosecone and Instrument Section for the Juno I first stage, has a decoupler on the nose. Separates from fuel tank after first stage burnout.

Name: FASAExplorerProbe
Title: Explorer 1 Probe
Description: Explorer 1, the first satellite launched by the United States, was a very simple scientific probe of less than a dozen kilograms. It featured a cosmic ray detector and micrometeorite detectors, as well as temperature sensors. Mercury batteries provided a month of electricity for the high power transmitter and another two and a half months for the low-power transmitter.

Name: FASAExplorerSgt
Title: Baby Sergeant (5.4KS1975)
Description: A small solid kick motor used on the Jupiter-C sounding rocket (and later the Juno I and II launch vehicles) as upper stages in clusters of 11, 3 and, finally, one attached to the payload. The standard version uses the T17-E2 grain mixture while the higher performance one uses the JPL-532A. Very low overall performance and reliability. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAExplorerSgt11
Title: Baby Sergeant 11x Solid Kick Motor Cluster
Description: First stage in the Sergeant Cluster used on Juno I and II launch vehicles and on the Jupiter-C test rocket. Uses T17-E2 fuel mixture, with lower performance than the JPL-532A fuel in the third and fourth stages. Attaches to the Baby Sergeant 11x decoupler. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAExplorerSgt11Dec
Title: Baby Sergeant 11x Cluster Decoupler
Description: A light decoupler for your Baby Sergeant 11x cluster. This attaches to the top of the Sergeant 3x rocket.

Name: FASAExplorerSgt3
Title: Baby Sergeant 3x Solid Kick Motor Cluster
Description: Middle cluster in Sergeant Cluster used on Juno I and II launch vehicles and on the Jupiter-C test rocket. Uses the high performance variant (JPL-532A). Attaches below 3x decoupler. Attach 11x decoupler below this. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: FASAExplorerSgt3Dec
Title: Baby Sergeant 3x Cluster Decoupler
Description: A small decoupler for your 3x Baby Sargent engine cluster.

Name: FASAFairingBase_15m
Title: Payload Launch Fairing Base [60"]
Description: A 60" PLF (payload launch fairing) base for Atlas and Agena-D payloads.

Name: FASAFairingBase_165m
Title: Payload Launch Fairing Base [65"]
Description: A 65" PLF (payload launch fairing) base for Agena-D payloads.

Name: FASAFairingBase_3m
Title: Payload Launch Fairing Base [120"]
Description: A 120" PLF (payload launch fairing) base is for Titan II and III series payloads.

Name: FASAFairingBase_43m
Title: Payload Launch Fairing Expanded Base [168"]
Description: A 168" PLF (payload launch fairing) base is for Titan IIIE and Commercial Titan III payloads.

Name: FASAFairingBase_508m
Title: Payload Launch Fairing Expanded Base [200"]
Description: A 200" PLF (payload launch fairing) base for Titan IV payloads.

Name: FASAFairingBase_76m
Title: 396" PLF Base/Decoupler
Description: This 396" PLF (payload launch fairing) base is for Saturn V-sized payloads

Name: FASAFairingNosecone_3mSRB
