Description: The TT-38K Radial Decoupler, like most other decouplers, is equipped with a (hopefully) small explosive charge, that will sever the structural linkage between itself and whatever it's connected to.

Name: radialDecoupler1-2

Name: RadialDrill

Description: Designed to help extract valuable resources from the crust of planets and asteroids, the Drill-O-Matic uses a rotary drill combined with an internal transfer auger to pull crushed regolith into holding tanks for later processing.  When operated by a skilled engineer, you will be able to operate with better efficiency.  These modules operate best at their ideal operating temperatures, and features auto-shutdown in the event of excessive overheating.  Radiators can be used to help manage excessive heat. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: radialDrogue

Name: rd100

Differs from the core engine series (RD-108) with a higher chamber pressure, thrust, and smaller vernier layout. The R-7 family core was supplemented for (roughly) two minutes by four strap-on boosters powered by these engines. Diameter: [1.85 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: RD108
Title: RD-108 Series
Description: Core engine for the R-7 Semyorka and its derivatives, including the Sputnik, Luna, Voskhod, Vostok, Soyuz, and Molniya launch vehicles.  Differs from the booster engine series (RD-107) with a lower chamber pressure, thrust, and a wider vernier layout.  Powers the R-7 family core through a very long (roughly) five minute burn that starts on the pad alongside the boosters. Diameter: [1.85 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: RD58
Title: S1.5400/RD-58 Series
Description: World's first closed-cycle kerolox vacuum engine. The S1.5400 served as an R-7 upper stage and the RD-58 (an upgrade) as upper stage / OMS for many Soviet and Russian launchers and spacecraft (Proton, N1, Zenit, Buran...). The S1.5400 was designed for the Blok L stage which was the final stage for the Molniya configuration of the R-7, used to launch communication satellites and interplanetary probes. Unlike prior upper stages, it was restartable (this was needed to perform apogee kick to place Molniya satellites in their final orbits). It was given the industry designation 11D33. An upgraded version, termed 11D33M, had slightly improved performance. The RD-58 is a derivative of the 11D33M engine with higher performance (industry designation 11D58); it has been used on many Russian launchers and is still in use today on Proton and Zenit. In comparison to hydrolox upper stages, kerolox ones do not suffer boiloff as badly and need far less volume (kerosene being far denser than liquid hydrogen), but have much lower specific impulse. Diameter: [2.0 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Description: This asssembly includes two Sabatier reactors for high ald low temperature conversion along with thermal exchangers to ensure most energy effective procession. (CO2 + H2 -> CH4 + H2O) (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: RealISRU_Hex_Tank

Name: RealISRU_Hex_Tank_b
Title: Hex Segment Tank variant b
Description: General 840 liter tank, holding everything you want. Mounts on one of ISRU Hex Cores. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: RealISRU_IceDrill
Title: Ice Drill
Description: Deployable drill for extracting water from ice and hydrates.  Includes a heating element to separate the liquid water automatically. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: RealISRU_LiquefactionArray
Title: Liquefaction Array
Description: Uses a combination of active cooling and pressurization turbines to convert gasses into liquids. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: RealISRU_MethanePyrolyzer
Title: Methane Pyrolysis Unit
Description: IN DEVELOPMENT: A small methane pyrolysis unit. CH4 --> C + 2 H2 (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: RealISRU_SabatierReactor
Title: Sabatier Reactor Unit
Description: IN DEVELOPMENT: A small Sabatier reactor unit. CO2 + 4 H2 --> CH4 + 2 H2O (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: RealISRU_SolidOxideElectrolyzer
Title: Solid Oxide Electrolysis Unit
Description: IN DEVELOPMENT: A small Solid Oxide electrolysis unit. 2 CO2 --> 2 CO + O2 (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: RealISRU_WaterElectrolyzer
Title: Water Electrolysis Unit
Description: IN DEVELOPMENT: A small water electrolysis unit. 2 H2O --> 2 H2 + O2 (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: RealISRU_WaterGasShift
Title: Water Gas Shift Unit
Description: IN DEVELOPMENT: A small Water Gas Shift unit. Can be run in reverse mode as well. CO + H2O --> CO2 + H2 REVERSE: CO2 + H2 --> CO + H2O (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: RelayAntenna100
Title: RA-100 Parabolic Antenna
Description: A fixed axial feed parabolic antenna for deep space telecommunications.

Name: RelayAntenna5
Title: RA-2 Parabolic Antenna
Description: A fixed Cassegrain parabolic antenna for general applications. Features a composite protective cover for the reflector.

Name: RelayAntenna50
Title: RA-15 Parabolic Antenna
Description: A fixed Gregorian - style parabolic antenna for deep space telecommunications.

Name: retinaGravimeter
Title: AIES Retina Gravimeter
Description: Measures the strength of gravity. Exactly what it says on the tin.

Name: RL10A-1
Title: RL10A-1
EntryCost: 60000, HydroloxPumps // guessed, plus sourced to cw

Name: RL10A-3-3
Title: RL10A-3-3
EntryCost: 80000, RL10A-3-1 // guessed plus sourced from cw

Name: RLA_large_frame
Title: M-LF Large Construction Frame
Description: Build the rover of your dreams with the super duper high tech Construction Frame!

Name: RLA_large_mptank
Title: FL-R200 MonoPropellant Tank
Description: An even bigger monopropellant tank for use with specialised engines, or if you need to do an awful lot of docking.

Name: RLA_lfo_medium_linearspike
Title: XRS-2200
Description: A linear aerospike engine developed for NASA's X-33 sub-scale SSTO technology demonstrator. Like the toroidal J-2T engines, the XRS-2200 used machinery derived from the J-2S. Diameter: [2.5 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: RLA_med2small_biadap
Title: TVR-20S Stack Bi-Adapter
Description: Converts a single 1.25m stack into two 0.625m stacks.

Name: RLA_med2small_quadadap
Title: TVR-40S Stack Quad-Adapter
Description: Converts a single 1.25m stack into four 0.625m stacks. Particularly useful for clustering engines.

Name: RLA_med2small_triadap
Title: TVR-30S Stack Tri-Adapter
Description: Converts a single 1.25m stack into three 0.625m stacks.

Name: RLA_medium_frame
Title: M-MF Medium Construction Frame
Description: A small frame with Maxo's brand new, patent-pending EZ Constructo-Grid that allows bolt on attachment of anything you can imagine. Please see Volume 12, Chapter 22, Page 516, Paragraph 8 of the Maxo Construction Builders Guide (on sale now!) for a full list of the parts you are allowed to imagine.

Name: RLA_medium_mptank
Title: FL-R50 MonoPropellant Tank
Description: A boring old tank of monopropellant, with a fetching paint scheme.

Name: RLA_medium_radext
Title: TVR-100R Radial Stack Extender
Description: Everyone loves wide stacks, and with the TVR-100R you can have the even widerest! This is not a decoupler.

Name: RLA_medium_solarpanel
Title: OX-9 1x2 Photovoltaic Panels
Description: A breakthrough product from little-known manufacturer Zaltonic, the OX-9 is designed to meet the electrically draining needs of todays active lifestyle. The panels are thin, fragile and cannot be retracted, so atmospheric surfing is not advised. 4.2m^2.

Name: RLA_mmrtg
Title: Multi-Mission RTG
Description: Multi-Mission Radioisotope Thermoelectric Generator or (MMRTG) developed by Aerojet Rocketdyne and Teledyne Energy Systems.

Name: RLA_mp_large_spike
Title: J-2T-200/250K
Description: Aerospike. Using proven technology from the J-2 and introducing an aerospike nozzle to the developing J-2S machinery. Diameter: [2.5 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: RLA_mp_large_vac
Title: RL60 Vacuum Engine
Description: Next generation cryogenic upper stage engine designed to replace the RL10, providing higher performance while maintaining the same installation envelope.  Also available in a lower 180kN thrust Vinci-180 model. Diameter: [1.5 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: RLA_mp_medium_vac
Title: TR-201
Description: Deeply throttleable pressure-fed vacuum engine used for the descent module of the Apollo lunar lander. Uses storable propellants which are not subject to boiloff, but are far less efficient than hydrolox or even kerolox. The version used on J-class missions had slightly higher specific impulse (this, along with other changes, gave enough payload capacity for the rover, for example). A later variant (TR-201) was used on Delta as an upper stage engine (on Delta P series); this was a low-cost model with more restarts (4 instead of 2) and slightly higher thrust but lower efficiency and no throttling capability. Diameter: [1.5 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: RLA_mp_small_fuelcell
Title: FC-1 MonoPropellant Fuel Cell
Description: The chemical conversion of monopropellant to electrical energy is extremely poorly understood, so using it on valuable spacecraft seems a sensible idea. Works best in situations where solar power isn't a viable option. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: RLA_mp_small_radial
Title: RD-0214
Description: A vernier engine cluster found on the third stage of the Proton series launcher. Diameter: [3.78 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: RLA_mp_small_stack
Title: MPR-5 "Cirrus" MonoPropellant Engine
Description: Designed to use monopropellant, the MPR-5 is ideal for use with small landers. Radial tanks are not recommended for use with the engine. Plume configured by RealPlume. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: RLA_mp_tiny_radial
Title: 0.5kN Class Thruster
Description: A small lightweight thruster for orbital maneuvers. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: RLA_mp_tiny_stack
Title: 0.5kN Class Thruster
Description: A small lightweight thruster for orbital maneuvers. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: RLA_rcs_2way
Title: RV-80 RCS Thruster Block
Description: One of the precursors to the RV-105, this unit only has bi-directional thrust. Great for simple translation maneuvers.

Name: RLA_rcs_5way
Title: RV-105-PLUS RCS Thruster Block
Description: Improving the venerable RV-105 seemed like a daunting task, and STEADLER Corps engineers wasted many hours arguing over the best way to do it. Eventually they gave up and just drilled a hole in the top and stuck another nozzle in it.

Name: RLA_rcs_5way_half
Title: RV-105-PLUS RCS Thruster Block (1/2)
Description: Improving the venerable RV-105 seemed like a daunting task, and STEADLER Corps engineers wasted many hours arguing over the best way to do it. Eventually they gave up and just drilled a hole in the top and stuck another nozzle in it.

Name: RLA_rcs_5way_quarter
Title: RV-105-PLUS RCS Thruster Block (1/4)
Description: Improving the venerable RV-105 seemed like a daunting task, and STEADLER Corps engineers wasted many hours arguing over the best way to do it. Eventually they gave up and just drilled a hole in the top and stuck another nozzle in it.

Name: RLA_rcs_linear
Title: RV-50 Linear RCS Port
Description: One of the early prototype units for the RCS Block we all know and love. Useful when a little extra kick is needed for vessel rotation, or balancing translation on very oddly changed vessels.

Name: RLA_rcs_micro
Title: RM-105 Micro RCS Block
Description: Extending STEADLERs product line further, these RCS thrusters should provide just enough thrust to dock a probe sized craft quickly, or a full sized craft slowly.

Name: RLA_rcs_micro_linear
Title: RM-50 Micro RCS Block
Description: A cut down alternative to regular RCS blocks with only a single nozzle for finetuning rotation or translation on smaller vehicles.

Name: RLA_rcs_micro45
Title: RM-105-45 Micro RCS Block
Description: Extending STEADLERs product line further, these RCS thrusters should provide just enough thrust to dock a probe sized craft quickly, or a full sized craft slowly. Designed for 45 degree offset placement to allow for cardinal direction translation. Useful on certain command pods and other components.

Name: RLA_rcs45
Title: RV-105-45 RCS Thruster Block
Description: Improving the venerable RV-105 seemed like a daunting task, and STEADLER Corps engineers wasted many hours arguing over the best way to do it. One of those options was altering the angle of the nozzles. Designed for 45 degree offset placement to allow for cardinal direction translation. Useful on certain command pods and other components.

Name: RLA_rcs45_2way
Title: RV-80-45 RCS Thruster Block
Description: One of the precursors to the RV-105, this unit only has offset bi-directional thrust. Designed for 45 degree offset placement to allow for cardinal direction translation. Useful on certain command pods and other components.

Name: RLA_small_arcjet
Title: MR-510 Arcjet
Description: Aerojet MR-510 series arcjet engines are currently used on Lockheed Martin A2100 satellites using hydrazine as a propellant. Diameter: [0.043 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: RLA_small_attach_radial
Title: BZ-13 Radial Attachment Point
Description: Perfect for attaching sideways facing engines, clusters of components on larger parts, or other similar nonsense.

Name: RLA_small_decoupler_radial
Title: TT-16 Radial Decoupler
Description: The TT-16 Radial Decoupler, like most other decouplers, is equipped with a small explosive charge, that will sever the structural linkage between itself and whatever it's connected to.

Name: RLA_small_decoupler_stack
Title: TR-1V Stack Decoupler
Description: The TR-1V Stack Decoupler is a miniature detachment utility for small rockets and space probes.

Name: RLA_small_highthrust
Title: RD-253/RD-275
Description: A high thrust engine designed for use with storable propellants. In use with the Proton series of rockets. Diameter: [2.0 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: RLA_small_ion
Title: XIPS ION Thruster
Description: Smaller cousin to the NSTAR or 30cm thruster good for station keeping or raising orbit. Diameter: [0.4 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: RLA_small_LFO_tank0
Title: FS-L10T Fuel Tank
Description: There are those in this world who like things small and neat, this teeny tiny tank is for them. Contains enough propellant to scare an unsuspecting Kerbal if misused.

Name: RLA_small_LFO_tank1
Title: FS-L20 Fuel Tank
Description: As fuel tanks go, this isn't the most impressive. But it's not about size, it's about how you use it.

Name: RLA_small_LFO_tank2
Title: FS-L30 Fuel Tank
Description: The S stands for small, and the L stands for little. This is not a cut down L40, despite appearances. Best put to use on small rockets or little landers.

Name: RLA_small_LFO_tank3
Title: FS-L40 Fuel Tank
Description: Why a checkerboard pattern? Why not a checkerboard pattern?

Name: RLA_small_LFO_tank4
Title: FS-L50 Fuel Tank
Description: Clearly the designer of this fuel tank had many pictures of stretched limousines decorating their office.

Name: RLA_small_mptank
Title: FL-R15 MonoPropellant Tank
Description: Monopropellant can be used for many things; stripping paint, docking spacecraft, cooking, powering engines, making fabulous cocktails, and even charging batteries. What will you use it for?

Name: RLA_small_ntr
Title: RS-88 Series
Description: High thrust pressure-fed hypergolic engine. Initially designed and built as a part of the NASA Bantam System Technology program, aiming for a low cost, high power propulsion system. It was later modified by Lockheed Martin for use as a launch abort engine. A derivative of the RS-88 is used by the Boeing CST-100 "Starliner" spacecraft for launch aborts under the name "Launch Abort Engine - LAE". Diameter: [1.9 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: RLA_small_probe_24sides
Title: Probodobodyne IKOTET
Description: Circular, cylindrical, curved. All very fine words, so fine in fact that Probodobodyne made a probe that was all of those things combined, and even stuck an advanced, heat resistant, automatic, computerised, electronic brain in there so it can do useful things like spin around. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: RLA_small_probe_24sides_gold
Title: Probodobodyne IKOTET-G
Description: Built from the most heat-resistant electronics and computers money can buy, wrapped in special insulating gold foil that looks much like regular gold foil but is actually very different, and a pricetag that cannot be matched by any other probe on the market. Order yours today! (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: RLA_small_probe_4sides
Title: Probodobodyne TET
Description: This is far more than a box of mere batteries, the TET is a lean, mean, electrically optimised machine! It's so optimised in fact it doesn't even have those fancy reaction wheely things, or that new fangled flight software. There was simply no more room left inside! (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: RLA_small_probe_4sides_gold
Title: Probodobodyne TET-G
Description: The dawn of a new age in big boxy probes, but now shiny and gold! For this special edition of the TET, a software update and even some low-power reaction wheels have been included, as well as behind the scenes videos and a directors commentary. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: RLA_small_probe_6sides_gold
Title: Probodobodyne HECS-G
Description: A common complaint that Prodobodyne receives is that probe cores aren't cool enough. To fix that, they found some very fancy looking gold foil and included it on their modernised product line. Across the board software upgrades and some advanced components make these updated probes stand out from the crowd, and the HECS in particular has some very capable reaction wheels to boot. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: RLA_small_probe_8sides_gold
Title: Probodobodyne OKTO-G
Description: While the OKTO2 was a very well received item, the venerable OKTO itself was still seeing some use as a cheap way of controlling basic satellites, probes and other unmanned vehicles. This update of that popular model has the full suite of guidance programs, though not much else. It is still fairly cheap though! (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: RLA_small_probe_QBE_gold
Title: Probodobodyne QBE-G
Description: When it was time to update the QBE, Prodobodyne were stumped. All the cool features had gone into their other products, and all they had left was a box of batteries and some foil left over. So they shrugged, put them on the QBE housing and called it a day. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: RLA_small_radext
Title: TVR-50R Radial Stack Extender
Description: Everyone loves wide stacks, and with the TVR-50R you can have the even widerest! This is not a decoupler.

Name: RLA_small_resistojet
Title: S5.92
Description: A gas generator cycle hypergolic vacuum engine. Used on the Fregat upper stage series. Diameter: 0.85 m. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: RLA_small_spike
Title: 36-5D "Caravel" Annular Aerospike Engine
Description: Experimental development within Rockomax has lead to the creation of this unusual engine. The standout feature is the single, circular (or annular) combustion chamber around the rim of the engine. This allows for thrust vectoring by directing fuel into different parts of the chamber, which leads to more or less thrust on different faces of the nozzle. The only drawbacks are the low thrust and it gets a bit warm after extended use. Plume configured by RealPlume. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: RLA_solid_medium_upper
Title: Orion 50 [1.25 m]
Description: A small booster developed as a low-cost, high performance second stage for the Pegasus Launch Vehicle. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: RLA_solid_small_long
Title: Castor 4AXL
Description: Small booster attached to larger rockets to give that extra thrust needed to get off the ground and/or with larger payloads. Slightly larger than it's siblings produces a bit more thrust. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: RLA_solid_small_medium
Title: Boostertron II Solid Fuel Booster
Description: The minds at Periapsis are not the most imaginative, so in attempting to capitalise on the usefulness of the Boostertron they could only come up with the idea of making it longer. Luckily though this worked out fairly well since a longer SRB ends up with a bunch more thrust. Perfect for helping overweight rockets off of the pad. Plume configured by RealPlume. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: RLA_solid_small_short
Title: Castor 4A
Description: Small booster attached to larger rockets to give that extra thrust needed to get off the ground and/or with larger payloads. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: RLA_tiny_mptank_rad
Title: Stratus-V Capsulated MonoPropellant Tank
Description: A very small radially attached monopropellant tank for those who don't like to be wasteful.

Name: RLA_tiny_torque_radial
Title: Tiny Radial Reaction Wheel
Description: A teeny tiny little spinning wheel rests inside a teeny tiny little gyroscope, allowing for rotational control of a spacecraft without having to use propellant to do it. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: RLA_tiny_vac
Title: R-4D-11
Description: 490N thrusters as found as the main propulsion of the ESA ATV, and used as various other control thrusters on numerous vehicles. Plume configured by RealPlume. (PART NOT COSTED BY RP-0 BUT IN CORRECT NODE)

Name: RLA_x_small_tank
Title: PB-X450 Xenon Container
Description: Probodobodynes response to seeing an increase in the useage of Xenon-propelled vehicles, a tank with more Xenon in!

Name: rn_7k_astp_lsolar
Title: Soyuz 19 ASTP Left Solar Array
Description: Soyuz ASTP series LEFT solar panels. (PART NOT COSTED BY RP-0 BUT IN CORRECT NODE)

Name: rn_7k_astp_rsolar
Title: Soyuz 19 ASTP Right Solar Array
Description: Soyuz ASTP series RIGHT solar panels. (PART NOT COSTED BY RP-0 BUT IN CORRECT NODE)

Name: rn_7k_zond_lsolar
Title: Soyuz 7K-L1 Zond Left Solar Array
Description: Soyuz 7K-L1 series LEFT solar panels.

Name: rn_7k_zond_rsolar
Title: Soyuz 7K-L1 Zond Right Solar Array
Description: Soyuz 7K-L1 series RIGHT solar panels.

Description: Parachute for nosecone of the Aerobee 100/150/150A/170/170A series rockets. Attach on top of the main tank and under the SAS module.

Name: rn_aerobee_payload_dec
Title: Aerobee 100/150/300 Payload Decoupler

Name: rn_aerobee100_mb
Title: Aerobee Jr 100 Fuel Tank
Description: Liquid fuel tank for the Aerobee Jr 100 sounding rocket. Powered by Aerobee Jr rocket engine.

Name: rn_aerobee150_eng
Title: AJ11 Rocket Engine
Description: A rocket engine used on the Aerobee 150/150A/300/300A. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: rn_aerobee150_eng1
Title: Aerobee Jr Rocket Engine
Description: A rocket engine used on the Aerobee 100.

Name: rn_aerobee150_fin
Title: Aerobee 150A/170A/300A Rocket Fin
Description: Place 4 of these on the bottom of the Aerobee 150A/170A/300A main body at 45 degree rotation.

Name: rn_aerobee150_fin2
Title: Aerobee 100/150/170/300 Rocket Fin
Description: Place 3 of these on the bottom of the Aerobee 100/150/170/300 main body at 120 degree angles.

Name: rn_aerobee150_mb
Title: Aerobee 150A/170A/300A Fuel Tank
Description: Liquid fuel tank for the Aerobee 150A/170A/300A sounding rocket. Powered by AJ11-6 rocket engine.

Name: rn_aerobee150_mb2
Title: Aerobee 150/170/300 Fuel Tank
Description: Liquid fuel tank for the Aerobee 150/170/300 sounding rocket. Powered by AJ11-21 rocket engine.

Name: rn_aerobee150_nc
Title: Aerobee 100/150/170 Nosecone
Description: Payload nosecone of the Aerobee 100/150/150A/170/170A. Contains experiments.

Name: rn_aerobee150_rcs
Title: Aerobee 100/150/170 RCS De-spin Module
Description: RCS de-spin module for the Aerobee 100/150/150A/170/170A. Place between the main body and SAS module.

Title: Aerobee 100/150/170 Probe Core

Name: rn_aerobee150_srb

Name: rn_aerobee170_srb_dec

Name: rn_aerobee300_nc_sas

Name: rn_aerobee300_srb_dec
Title: Aerobee 300 Third Stage SRB Decoupler
Description: Decoupler for the Aerobee 300/300A third stage.

Description: A rocket engine used on the Aerobee 350. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: rn_aerobee350_nc

Description: Decoupler for the Aerobee 350 SRB. Attach between the SRB and main body.

Name: rn_aj10_104
Title: AJ10 Upper Stage Engine Extended
Description: Small pressure-fed hypergolic upper stage engine. Derivative of the first US liquid rocket engine, the AJ10 series is perhaps the longest-lived of any engine series, a part of the US's first satellite launch vehicle, Vanguard, the Apollo CSM, and even one projected Orion service module. This represents mid-period AJ10s with a nozzle extension and restart capability. Used on Thor-Ablestar/Epsilon and Delta E through Delta N. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: rn_aj10_37
Title: AJ10 Upper Stage Engine
Description: Small pressure-fed hypergolic upper stage engine for the Thor-Able/Delta. Derivative of the first US liquid rocket engine, the AJ10 series is perhaps the longest-lived of any engine series, a part of the US's first satellite launch vehicle, Vanguard, the Apollo CSM, and even one projected Orion service module. This is the original Vanguard second stage / Able / Delta configuration, without restart capability. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: rn_almaz_fairing
Title: Almaz Proton Fairing
Description: Fairing for the Almaz station for use with the Proton. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Description: Docking port for ASTP

Description: Grate to place on top of descent tank upper.

Description: Orbital module for the ASTP. (Missing entryCost field) (PART NOT COSTED BY RP-0 BUT IN CORRECT NODE)

Title: R7 Block L Ullage Stage
Description: Ullage base for Block L of Molniya rocket. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Description: Vernier engine for use on Block L. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Description: Briz-M for use with Proton.

Title: S5.98M
