Title: Vinci Vacuum Engine [2.5 m]
Description: Vinci is a European Space Agency cryogenic liquid rocket engine currently under development. It is designed to power the new upper stage of Ariane 5, ESC-B, and will be the first European re-ignitable cryogenic upper stage engine, raising the launcher's GTO performances to 12 t. Mount size can be adjusted from 1.25m to 10m in 1m increments. Name: SSTU-SC-GEN-DP-0P
Title: Apollo Docking System
Description: The Apollo Docking System.  This is an androgynous spacecraft docking and berthing mechanism developed for the Apollo space program.

Name: SSTU-SC-GEN-DP-1P
Title: NASA Docking System
Description: The NASA Docking System (NDS) is a spacecraft docking and berthing mechanism being developed for future US human spaceflight vehicles, such as the Orion Multi-Purpose Crew Vehicle and the Commercial Crew vehicles. The NDS is NASA's implementation of the International Docking System Standard (IDSS), an attempt by the ISS Multilateral Coordination Board (MCB) to create an international spacecraft docking standard. NDS is also known as the international Low Impact Docking System (iLIDS). Parachutes included.

Includes both top and internal payload decouplers.  Has configurable height and diameter.

This model features an integrated inverted taper below the fairing mounting point.  Includes both top and internal payload decouplers.  Has configurable height and diameter.

Name: SSTU-SC-GEN-ISDC

Name: SSTU-SC-GEN-PDC

Compact when folded up, and with a decent energy density, the Station Core line of solar panels are an effective means of long term energy generation.  This model features multiple-axis solar tracking for a more consistent energy output regardless of vessel orientation. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SSTU-ST-GEN-DSP-ISS
Title: SSTU - ST-GEN - DSP-ISS
Description: SSTU - StationCore: Deployable Solar Panel - Incredibly Super Sized.  This is what happens when you tell your engineers that 'size is no limitation!'. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SSTU-ST-GEN-DSP-MAX-L
Title: SSTU - ST-GEN - DSP-MAX-L
Description: SSTU - StationCore: Deployable Solar Panel - MAX-L - The 'Multi-AXis' line of solar panels was a breakthrough in the application of the 'more is better' school of engineering.  The designers added a second set of servomotors to the tracking system of the solar panel allowing it to track the sun on multiple axis, resulting in more consistent and reliable energy generation. Compact when folded up, and with a decent energy density, the Station Core line of solar panels are an effective means of long term energy generation. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Title: SSTU - ST-GEN - DSP-SMA-L
Description: SSTU - StationCore - Deployable Solar Panel - SMA-L - The 'Service Module' series of solar panels was, surprisingly, not the result of a large and expensive research project.  Instead of hiring a team of costly engineers and scientists, the project lead gave some unpaid interns a box of model solar panel parts and chose the best of the resulting designs.  Regardless, we think they work well for stations, service modules, and probes.  Compact when folded up, and with a decent energy density, the Station Core line of solar panels are an effective means of long term energy generation. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Title: SSTU - ST-GEN - WDP - Welding Docking Port
Description: SSTU - Ship Core: General - Welding Docking Port.  Dock two of these together, retract the push-rings, and press the 'Weld' button for a permanent station construction alternative. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SSTU-ST-HAB-A1
Title: SSTU - ST-HAB-A1
Description: SSTU - StationCore - HAB-A1 - 1.25m Inflatable Habitat Module - Short.  Includes accommodations for 2 crew when inflated, and requires 0.621t of construction materials to inflate while in the field. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SSTU-ST-HAB-A2
Title: SSTU - ST-HAB-A2
Description: SSTU - StationCore - HAB-A2 - 1.25m Inflatable Habitat Module - Long.  Includes accommodations for 3 crew when inflated, and requires 0.942t of construction materials to inflate while in the field. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SSTU-ST-HAB-B1
Title: SSTU - ST-HAB-B1
Description: SSTU - StationCore - HAB-B1 - 2.5m Inflatable Habitat Module - Short.  Includes accommodations for 10 crew when inflated, and requires 1.9905t of construction materials to inflate while in the field.  Includes service module with integrated RCS thrusters, airlock, and optional solar panels. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SSTU-ST-HAB-B2
Title: SSTU - ST-HAB-B2
Description: SSTU - StationCore - HAB-B2 - 2.5m Inflatable Habitat Module - Long.  Includes accommodations for 15 crew when inflated, and requires 2.883t of construction materials to inflate while in the field.  Includes service module with integrated RCS thrusters, airlock, and optional solar panels. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SSTU-ST-HAB-B3
Title: SSTU - ST-HAB-B3
Description: SSTU - StationCore - HAB-B3 - 2.5m Inflatable Habitat Module - Short.  Includes accommodations for 10 crew when inflated, and requires 2.052t of construction materials to inflate while in the field. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SSTU-ST-HAB-B4
Title: SSTU - ST-HAB-B4
Description: SSTU - StationCore - HAB-B4 - 2.5m Inflatable Habitat Module - Long.  Includes accommodations for 15 crew when inflated, and requires 3.084t of construction materials to inflate while in the field. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Title: SSTU - ST-HAB-C1
Description: SSTU - StationCore - HAB-C1 - 3.75m Inflatable Habitat Module - Short. Description: SSTU - StationCore - HAB-C2 - 3.75m Inflatable Habitat Module - Long.  Deploys to 7.5m diameter when fully inflated, can accommodate 36, and requires 6.492t of construction materials to inflate while in the field.  Includes service module with integrated RCS thrusters, airlock, and optional solar panels. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SSTU-ST-HAB-C3
Title: SSTU - ST-HAB-C3
Description: SSTU - StationCore - HAB-C3 - 3.75m Inflatable Habitat Module - Short.  Includes accommodations for 24 crew when inflated, and requires 4.644t of construction materials to inflate while in the field. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SSTU-ST-HAB-C4
Title: SSTU - ST-HAB-C4
Description: SSTU - StationCore - HAB-C4 - 3.75m Inflatable Habitat Module - Long.  Deploys to 7.5m diameter when fully inflated, can accommodate 36, and requires 6.948t of construction materials to inflate while in the field. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SSTU-ST-HUB-COS
Title: SSTU - ST-HUB-COS - Docking Hub
Description: SSTU - Station Core: Docking Hub - COS variant.  Includes some habitable area, though there is no external access and no included provisions for long term habitation.  Bring your own snacks. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SSTU-ST-HUB-DOS
Title: SSTU - ST-HUB-DOS - Docking Hub
Description: SSTU - Station Core: Docking Hub - DOS variant. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SSTU-ST-MST-ISS
Title: SSTU - ST-MST-ISS - Modular Solar Truss
Description: SSTU - StationCore: Modular Solar Truss - Multi-Panel, Multi-Axis solar panel truss segment.  Includes two extra-large DSP-ISS panels mounted on a secondary sun-tracking pivot. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: stackBiCoupler
Title: TVR-200 Stack Bi-Coupler
Description: The TVR-200 Stack Bi-Coupler is a simple method for splitting one rocket into two - WITHOUT the disastrous consequences of doing it the normal (explosive) way.

Name: stackDecoupler
Title: TR-18A Stack Decoupler
Description: The TR-18A Stack Decoupler is equipped with a (hopefully) small explosive charge, that will sever the structural linkage between itself and whatever it's connected to. Painted on its sides are handy arrows indicating which side will detach.

Name: stackDecouplerMini
Title: TR-2V Stack Decoupler
Description: The TR-2V Stack Decoupler is a miniature detachment utility for small rockets and space probes.

Name: stackPoint1
Title: BZ-52 Radial Attachment Point
Description: Originally a defective Clamp-O-Tron docking port, engineers soon discovered it had great potential as a structural element.

Name: stackQuadCoupler
Title: TVR-2160C Mk2 Stack Quad-Coupler
Description: What could be more awesome than a Tricoupler? Why, a quadcoupler, of course. Just remember that this is not a decoupler, and will not separate stages.

Name: stackSeparator
Title: TR-18D Stack Separator
Description: Unlike Decouplers, Separators jettison everything attached to them. This new technology was very well received by rocket engineers everywhere. Not bad for something that started out as a failure for a controlled explosive bolt prototype.

Name: stackSeparatorBig
Title: TR-XL Stack Separator
Description: The TR-XL Stack Separator is the largest available from O.M.B, designed for slicing the largest of rockets in twain. Unlike Decouplers, Separators will eject anything connected to themselves. This is good, as it removes the need to worry about which side needs to be pointed away from face. Try to not look at it too much though.

Name: stackSeparatorMini
Title: TR-2C Stack Separator
Description: Similarly to the TR-18D, the TR-2C is a utility for slicing a rocket into two halves, but now in a more compact size. The manual says the explosive content is just enough to eject anything attached to the unit in a safe, controlled manner. The delivery guy did have a full bomb suit on though, so try not to drop it.

Name: stackTriCoupler
Title: TVR-1180C Mk1 Stack Tri-Coupler
Description: The Stack Tricoupler! If your stack is lacking in awesomeness, this is the tool for you! Just remember that this is not a decoupler, and won't separate stages.

Name: StandardCtrlSrf
Title: Elevon 1
Description: Made from the finest materials at hand, these flight surfaces are guaranteed to operate while attached to the craft. However studies have shown that a lack of atmosphere *may* slightly impede function. No refunds.

Name: standardNoseCone
Title: Small Nose Cone
Description: An aerodynamic nose cap.

Name: STAR5D
Title: STAR 5D (RAD)
Description: The STAR 5D rocket motor was designed and qualified to serve as the rocket-assisted deceleration (RAD) motor on the Mars Pathfinder mission. Three of these motors were fired to slow the Pathfinder spacecraft to near-zero velocity before bouncing on the surface of Mars. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: STAR8
Title: STAR 8 (RAD)
Description: The STAR 8 was developed and qualified as the rocket assisted deceleration (RAD) motor for the Mars Exploration Rover (MER) program. The motor is based on the STAR 5D motor technology developed for JPLs Mars Pathfinder program. The STAR 8 first flew in January 2004 when three motors were used to decelerate each of the Spirit and Opportunity rovers for landing at Gusev Crater and Meridiani Planum on Mars. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: stationHub
Title: Rockomax HubMax Multi-Point Connector
Description: When it was unveiled at the 3rd annual Rockets & Explosions festival, the HubMax Multi-Point Connector caused several patrons to die of shock on the spot. 'All my life I thought rocket parts could be placed one way - up! But Rockomax today has shattered that notion' said one survivor, who asked to remain anonymous. Needless to say, this part may very well herald a revolution in construction technologies. Docking ports sold separately.

Name: stationHubLarge
Title: Large Rockomax HubMax Multi-Point Connector
Description: After the fervorous response from fans, Rockomax has decide to up the ante with the Extra-Large Rockomax HubMax Multi-Point Connector, seamlessly integrating 2.5 meter parts on a very large hub. Unfortunately, no one died of shock that day.

Name: STEERING_MOTOR_RD0110engine
Title: RD-0110 Vernier
Description: The vernier engine for the RD-0110 power plant. Four of them are used on the Block I upper stage of the Soyuz U and FG launch vehicle variants for attitude control. Diameter: 0.3 m Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: structuralIBeam1
Title: M-Beam 650 I-Beam
Description: A wide, upscaled version of the M-Beam 200 I-Beam. Dinkelstein loves variety, man.

Name: structuralIBeam2
Title: M-Beam 200 I-Beam
Description: Handcrafted by Dinkelstein himself, the M-Beam 200 works great for making rockets and skyscrapers alike.

Name: structuralIBeam3
Title: M-Beam 200 I-Beam Pocket Edition
Description: Handcrafted by Dinkelstein himself, the M-Beam 200 works great for making rockets and skyscrapers alike. This one's half as long as the normal version, for building smaller skyscrapers and/or rockets.

Name: structuralMiniNode
Title: The Not-Rockomax Micronode
Description: Dinkelstein Kerman's Construction Emporium vehemently denies any and all accusations of industrial espionage arising from similarities between this product and a product-which-will-not-be-named from Rockomax Brand.

Name: structuralPanel1
Title: M-1x1 Structural Panel
Description: A sturdy metal plate, perfect for constructing all sorts of things.

Name: structuralPanel2
Title: M-2x2 Structural Panel
Description: Four M-1x1 have been arranged in a 2x2 layout for this part, then stuck together with super glue.

Name: structuralPanel3
Title: M-3x3 Structural Panel
Description: Nine M-1x1 have been arranged in a 3x3 layout for this part, then stuck together with two-part epoxy, none of that namby pamby super glue. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: structuralPylon
Title: Structural Pylon
Description: A structural Pylon for engine Support. Designed to fit against fuselages, and hull bodies. Comes Equipped with emergency bolts to separate jet engines in the event of fire or catastrophic failure. (Not covered by warranty)

Name: structuralWing
Title: Structural Wing Type A
Description: This wing has been constructed out of surplus wing components. Comes complete with "like new" finish. Intended uses include very large canards, and leading edges of larger delta wings.

Name: structuralWing2
Title: Structural Wing Type B
Description: This wing has been constructed out of surplus wing components. Comes complete with "like new" finish.

Name: structuralWing3
Title: Structural Wing Type C
Description: This wing has been constructed out of surplus wing components. Comes complete with "like new" finish.

Name: structuralWing4
Title: Structural Wing Type D
Description: This wing has been constructed out of surplus wing components. Comes complete with "like new" finish.

Name: strutConnector
Title: EAS-4 Strut Connector
Description: The Strut Connector is highly regarded by many spacecraft engineers as they help in constructing more stable spacecraft. Once both sides are connected, a structural beam is created to link both ends, allowing for sturdier (and heavier) construction.

Name: strutConnectorHeavy
Title: EAS-4 Strut Connector Heavy
Description: The Strut Connector is highly regarded by many spacecraft engineers as they help in constructing more stable spacecraft. Once both sides are connected, a structural beam is created to link both ends, allowing for sturdier (and heavier) construction.

Name: strutConnectorMedium
Title: EAS-4 Strut Connector Medium
Description: The Strut Connector is highly regarded by many spacecraft engineers as they help in constructing more stable spacecraft. Once both sides are connected, a structural beam is created to link both ends, allowing for sturdier (and heavier) construction.

Name: strutCube
Title: Cubic Octagonal Strut Mk I
Description: Now, with advances in technology, StrutCo brings you the Cubic Octagonal Strut - it's like a regular Octagonal Strut, but in the shape of a cube!

Name: strutCube3way
Title: Cubic Octagonal Strut Three Way Connector
Description: New from Strutco! A new connector that connects at right angles, and in two directions! Radical!

Name: strutCube90
Title: Cubic Octagonal Strut Angle Connector
Description: New from Strutco! A new connector that connects at right angles! Brilliant!

Name: strutCubeLarge
Title: Cubic Octagonal Strut Mk IV
Description: Now you can strut the gaps between your dreams, the Cubic Octagonal Strut MK IV is here!

Name: strutCubeMedium
Title: Cubic Octagonal Strut Mk III
Description: A Cubic Octagonal Strut that's even longer! Use multiple struts no longer! With these ultra-light extensions, you can now strut all the things!

Name: strutCubeMountingPlate
Title: Cubic Octagonal Strut Slim Mounting Plate
Description: A slim strut perfect for mounting things on other things!

Name: strutCubeOCTOAdapter
Title: Cubic Octagonal Strut Octagonal Adapter
Description: An adapter that connects your Standard C.O.S. into the standard Octagonal frame.

Name: strutCubeS0Adapter
Title: Cubic Octagonal Strut 0.625m Adapter
Description: An adapter that connects your Standard C.O.S. into the standard 0.625m frame.

Name: strutCubeSmall
Title: Cubic Octagonal Strut Mk II
Description: Despite its title, the Small Cubic Octagonal Strut is actually longer than its smaller cousin!

Name: strutOcto
Title: Octagonal Strut
Description: StrutCo presents: Octagonal struts! Use them to mount stop signs or octopi.

Name: strutsoportec1
Title: AIES C1 Support Strut
Description: This structural support adds some space between sections, you may find it useful in some of your designs.

Name: STXCANIOT
Title: PPD-H Crew Cabin
Description: Hold 6 people with 107 days of supplies. Probodobodyne Inc first and only foray into crew habitation modules. Bulky, but not uncomfortable. It even features a handy set of exterior handrails.

Name: SuperDraco_Double
Title: Twin SuperDraco
Description: SuperDraco is a hypergolic propellant liquid rocket engine designed and built by SpaceX. It is part of SpaceX's Draco family of rocket engines. A redundant array of eight SuperDraco engines provides fault-tolerant propulsion for use as a launch escape system and propulsive-landing thrust for the Dragon V2 passenger-carrying space capsule. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: SuperDraco_Single
Title: SuperDraco
Description: A powerful hypergolic engine. Used by the Dragon V2 Command Module for powered landings, trajectory corrections and as a Launch Abort System (LAS). Other applications include hypersonic deceleration and landing for crew and cargo modules. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: SuperDrago
Title: SuperDraco Dual Engine Block
Description: The integrated dual SuperDraco engine block used by the Dragon V2 spacecraft for powered landings, trajectory corrections and as a Launch Abort System (LAS).

Name: SUPERSTRUTCONNECTOR
Title: EAS-16 Strut Connector
Description: A high strength structural connector.

Name: SurfaceScanner
Title: Surface Scanning Module
Description: A small module that includes soil, atmospheric, and oceanic sampling tools.  When used while landed on a planet or moon, the sample data gathered can be used to increase the accuracy of orbital survey scanners. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SurfAntenna
Title: Communotron 16-S
Description: A short range omnidirectional antenna. Perfect for reentry vehicles and landers.

Name: SurveyScanner
Title: M700 Survey Scanner
Description: This orbital survey scanner uses a combination of advanced sensor technology and witchcraft to provide information on a planet or moons natural resources.  These images can be viewed either in flight, or in relative safety and comfort back at the KSC.  Be sure to bring an antenna capable of transmitting the information back, and sufficient power. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: sweptWing
Title: Swept Wings
Description: A prototype swept back wing, part of our "Let's Fly", line. Made of light weight composite materials. Guaranteed to generate lift, not guaranteed to ensure crew safety.

Name: sweptWing1
Title: Swept Wing Type A
Description: This wing has been constructed out of surplus wing components. Comes complete with "like new" finish.

Name: sweptWing2
Title: Swept Wing Type B
Description: This wing has been constructed from surplus wing components. Comes complete with "like new" finish.

Name: SXT_Jumo213A
Title: Junkers Jumo 213A
Description: WWII-era V-12 liquid-cooled piston engine, the Jumo 213A as produced by Junkers (GER).  2-speed, 1-stage supercharger.  Used on the Focke-wulfe Fw 190 D-9. 2100PS with MW50 injection, 1750PS dry.

Name: SXT-TMA1
Title: Tycho Magnetic Anomaly 1
Description: 1 : 4 : 9 (25 : 36 : n^2 ?) (Missing entryCost field) (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXT16FuelTank
Title: Kerbodyne KX200-16 Propellant Tank
Description: Developed as a direct competitor to Rockomax's X-200 series of tank. Largely identical, this has been covered in fancy paint and tubes to appeal to the more discerning engineer.

Name: SXT25mMk2Adap
Title: Mk2 to 2.5m Adapter Long
Description: A generic Mk2 to 2.5m adapter that was left to dry a bit too long and stretched out. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXT25mMk2AdapSlant
Title: Mk2 to 2.5m Adapter Slanted
Description: A generic Mk2 to 2.5m adapter that was knocked sideways. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXT25to375mKossak
Title: C7 Brand Adapter - 3.75m to 2.5m
Description: Often used in the design of larger aricraft. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXT32FuelTank
Title: Kerbodyne KX200-32 Propellant Tank
Description: Developed as a direct competitor to Rockomax's X-200 series of tank. Largely identical, this has been covered in fancy paint and tubes to appeal to the more discerning engineer.

Name: SXT375mProbe
Title: Saturn I Instrument Unit
Description: Guidance ring used for early Saturn I launches. Allows full control over the vessel, up to the tonnage limit (cumulative).

Name: SXT5m5wayAdaptor
Title: TVR-500XXL Stack Pent-Adapter
Description: Initially built due to a mis-read procurement form, the TVR-1600XXL units now take up a large portion of O.M.B.'s storage floor-space. It is now being sold under a variety of names, including 'My first Quad adaptor' and 'Self assembly pool', in order to clear the stock. Converts a single 5m stack into four 2.5m stacks. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXT5mQuadAdaptor
Title: TVR-1600XXL Stack Quad-Adapter
Description: Initially built due to a mis-read procurement form, the TVR-1600XXL units now take up a large portion of O.M.B.'s storage floor-space. It is now being sold under a variety of names, including 'My first Quad adaptor' and 'Self assembly pool', in order to clear the stock. Converts a single 5m stack into four 2.5m stacks. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXT5mTank0
Title: Kerbodyne S5-08000 Propellant Tank
Description: Kerbodyne's experimental ultra-heavy fuel tank. Tiny and flat, since we kept knocking the bigger ones over.

Name: SXT5mTank0cap
Title: Kerbodyne S5 Nose Cone Propellant Tank
Description: A fuelled nose-cone for Kerbodyne's experimental ultra-heavy fuel tank. While the KDB argues that Kerbodyne stole the design from them, Kerbodyne has reminded them that they can de-orbit space stations, and are getting very good at calculating where it they land.

Name: SXT625mFuel4
Title: OX - 4 Propellant Tank
Description: A small, general purpose, propellant tank.

Name: SXT64FuelTank
Title: Kerbodyne KX200-64 Propellant Tank
Description: Developed as a direct competitor to Rockomax's X-200 series of tank. Largely identical, this has been covered in fancy paint and tubes to appeal to the more discerning engineer.

Name: SXTadapterSize3Mk3
Title: M-Hull 3.75m to Mk3 Adapter Hollow
Description: A hollow adapter for when your craft turns from a massive rocket into a gargantuan plane! (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXTAirbag
Title: Mk10-XL Inflatable Airbag
Description: A set of inflatable balloons that can handle impacts of moderate speed on planetary surfaces. These airbags are well suited for landing small landers and probes on rough terrain when a skycrane or internal propulsion is lacking or imprecise. First used on Russian Luna landers like Luna 9, airbags served well as Mars landing systems during various missions.

Name: SXTAirbagSmall
Title: Mk-10 Inflatable Airbag
Description: A more advanced alternative to the Mk-10 landing system. Rather stronger.

Name: SXTAirbrake
Title: A.I.R.B.R.A.K.E.S "Panel"
Description: Slows you down. Like a bit, just a wee bit. You're basically still going to be travelling really fast. And will probably still crash. But you'll get about 2 extra seconds before hand. So that's nice. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXTAirbrakeLarge
Title: A.I.R.B.R.A.K.E.S "Surf"
Description: Slows you down. Well, providing you're in an atmosphere. It won't help on the Mun, unlike parachutes which definitely work there. Honest guv. Also doubles as a handy surfboard. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXTAirbrakeLarger
Title: A.I.R.B.R.A.K.E.S "Senior"
Description: Used for slowing planes down, can handily be placed next to control surfaces on wings. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: sxtairlockAnimated
Title: Airlock
Description: The airlock was designed shortly after the term 'Explosive Decompression' was coined. It allows Kerbals to move from the interior of the vessel to the exterior without a great change in internal pressure. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXTAJ10
Title: AJ10 Series (Early)
Description: Small pressure-fed hypergolic upper stage engine. Derivative of the first US liquid rocket engine, the AJ10 series is perhaps the longest-lived of any engine series, a part of the US's first satellite launch vehicle, Vanguard, the Apollo CSM, and even one projected Orion service module. This is the original Vanguard second stage / Able / Delta configuration, without restart capability. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: SXTAJ10Adv
Title: AJ10 Series (Advanced)
Description: Small pressure-fed hypergolic upper stage engine. Derivative of the first US liquid rocket engine, the AJ10 series is perhaps the longest-lived of any engine series, a part of the US's first satellite launch vehicle, Vanguard, the Apollo CSM, and even one projected Orion service module. This represents advanced era AJ10s with a nozzle extension and restart capability. Used on Transtage as AJ10-138; similar models but back with the -118 designation were used on the Delta F and Delta K upper stages. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: SXTAJ10Mid
Title: AJ10 Series (Mid)
Description: Small pressure-fed hypergolic upper stage engine. Derivative of the first US liquid rocket engine, the AJ10 series is perhaps the longest-lived of any engine series, a part of the US's first satellite launch vehicle, Vanguard, the Apollo CSM, and even one projected Orion service module. This represents mid-period AJ10s with a nozzle extension and restart capability. Used on Thor-Ablestar and Delta E through Delta N. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: SXTAlouetteI
Title: Alouette Core
Description: Alouette 1 and 2 were the first Canadian satellites launched in 1962 and 1963 with the purpose of studying the upper ionospheric layers of the Earth.

Name: SXTAn225Ramp
Title: Kn-225 Loading Ramp
Description: While not quite as sophisticated as the ramp mounted on the Mk3, it does allow for easy mounting to any surface. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXTAntenna
Title: Sputnik PS-1 Antenna
Description: Small whip antenna for the Sputnik PS-1 satellite.

Name: SXTBalloon
Title: XC-32 Inflatable Fuel Tank
Description: Although far more delicate and with slightly less fuel capacity for its size than the X200-32, it does boast a lower dry mass per fuel tonne. Perfect for orbital missions. Not recommended for landings. (Missing entryCost field) (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXTBalloon375
Title: OX-32 Inflatable Fuel Tank
Description: Although far more delicate and with slightly less fuel capacity for its size than the X200-32, it does boast a lower dry mass per fuel tonne. Perfect for orbital missions. Not recommended for landings. (Missing entryCost field) (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXTBalloonGold
Title: XC-32 Inflatable Fuel Tank [Gold]
Description: Although far more delicate and with slightly less fuel capacity for its size than the X200-32, it does boast a lower dry mass per fuel tonne. Perfect for orbital missions. Not recommended for landings. (Missing entryCost field) (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXTBalloonGold375
Title: OX-32-S Inflatable Fuel Tank
Description: Although far more delicate and with slightly less fuel capacity for its size than the X200-32, it does boast a lower dry mass per fuel tonne.  This version, while it can be configured for different fuels, only has a single tank.  Perfect for orbital missions. Not recommended for landings. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXTBalloonGoldB
Title: XC-32 Light Fuel Tank
Description: The lack of proper structural supports makes this fuel bladder extremely delicate and prevents the stacking of multiple cells on top of each other. Probably best not even lean against it. (Missing entryCost field) (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXTBalloonGoldB375
Title: XX-32 Light Fuel Tank (Gold)
Description: The lack of proper structural supports makes this fuel bladder extremely delicate and prevents the stacking of multiple cells on top of each other. Probably best not even lean against it. (Missing entryCost field) (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXTBlackAdder
Title: Gamma 8
Description: This was an 8 chamber development of Gamma, used for the first stage of the Black Arrow satellite launch vehicle. Gamma thrust chambers were mounted in pairs radially, each pair on a one-axis tangential gimbal. Collective movement gave roll control, differential movement pitch. Diameter: [1.98 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: SXTBlackAdder2
Title: Gamma 2
Description: A two chamber version of Gamma, used for the second stage of the Black Arrow satellite launch vehicle. As the only Gamma not required to operate at sea level, the nozzles were extended to allow better expansion. Diameter: [1.37 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: SXTBuzzard
Title: Junkers Ju-87 cockpit
Description: Cockpit for the Junkers Ju-87 also known as Stuka (from Sturzkampfflugzeug - dive bomber), two-man (pilot and rear gunner) German dive bomber and ground-attack aircraft.

Name: SXTcapsuleshield
Title: CTR-20A Capsule Shield
Description: Capsule shield (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXTCargoBay1
Title: C-130 Cargobay
Description: Cargobay of the C-130 Hercules, diameter is 3.75m.

Name: SXTCastor30
Title: STAR 17
Description: Small apogee kick motor for satellites, introduced in 1968 on Delta 57. Max thrust 12.34kN, burn time 18 seconds. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: SXTClyde
Title: DHC-3 Otter cockpit
Description: Cockpit for the DHC-3 Otter - single-engined, high-wing, propeller-driven, short take-off and landing (STOL) aircraft developed by de Havilland Canada.

Name: SXTCommodore
Title: RD-0120
Description: 1980s medium TWR, atmospheric and vacuum use. The RD-0120 is a fuel-rich staged combustion engine developed to power the core stage of the Energia launcher. Diameter: [3.5 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: SXTCrewCabSSP10
Title: PPD-4 Crew Cabin
Description: Hold 2 people with 23 days of supplies. A slightly cramped early station module. Features usable handle bars around the side.

Name: SXTCrewCabSSP20
Title: PPD-6 Crew Cabin
Description: Hold 4 people with 23 days of supplies. A slightly cramped early station module. Features usable handle bars around the side.

Name: SXTDepolyRTGI
Title: GPHS-RTG
Description: The General Purpose Heat Source - Radioisotope Thermoelectric Generator as found on the Galileo spacecraft.

Name: SXTDepolyRTGII
Title: GPHS-RTG [Shielded]
Description: The General Purpose Heat Source - Radioisotope Thermoelectric Generator as found on the Galileo spacecraft. Includes a protective cover.

Name: SXTDLK83EHabitat
Title: Ares LK-S3E Heavy Planetary Habitat
Description: Hold 8 people with 45 days of supplies. A top of the line habitat meant for long-term operations. Typically after the initial 'colonists' made their situation more 'permanent' with a bit of lithobreaking. Features cabins, food preparation areas, sofas, space loos, laboratory, and even a home gym.

Name: SXTdockingPortVeryLarge
Title: Clamp-O-Tron Docking Port XL.
Description: The Clamp-O-Tron X3. is an evolution of the Sr. Designed after the initial release of the Sr was met with, 'Ah, okay cool. Now make an even bigger one!'. When will the madness stop? (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXTeFan
Title: IX-eFAN "Esteyne" Electric Ducted Fan
Description: A state of the art electric ducted-fan engine. While not especially powerful, it does not require oxygen, making it perfect for use with probes on other atmospheric planets. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXTelevonLarge
Title: Elevon Mk2
Description: Made from the finest materials at hand, these flight surfaces are guaranteed to operate while attached to the craft. However studies have shown that a lack of atmosphere *may* slightly impede function. No refunds. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RO BUT PLACED AND COSTED BY RP-0)

Name: SXTelevonSmall
Title: Elevon 0-A
Description: Made from the finest materials at hand, these flight surfaces are guaranteed to operate while attached to the craft. However studies have shown that a lack of atmosphere *may* slightly impede function. No refunds. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RO BUT PLACED AND COSTED BY RP-0)

Name: SXTelevonSmallHalf
Title: Elevon 0-B
Description: Made from the finest materials at hand, these flight surfaces are guaranteed to operate while attached to the craft. However studies have shown that a lack of atmosphere *may* slightly impede function. No refunds. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RO BUT PLACED AND COSTED BY RP-0)

Name: SXTelevonVeryLarge
Title: Elevon Mk3
Description: Made from the finest materials at hand, these flight surfaces are guaranteed to operate while attached to the craft. However studies have shown that a lack of atmosphere *may* slightly impede function. No refunds. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RO BUT PLACED AND COSTED BY RP-0)

Name: SXTengineattachment
Title: FAT-50 Structural Pylon
Description: A structural pylon for engine support. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXTengineattachment2
Title: FAT-55 Structural Pylon
Description: A structural pylon for engine support. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXTEntenteCordiale
Title: Concorde cockpit
Description: Cockpit for the Aerospatiale-BAC Concorde, turbojet-powered, supersonic, passenger jet airliner.

Name: SXTfairingSize0
Title: AE-FF0 Airstream Protective Shell (0.625m)
Description: While the Kerbals at Mission Control were still figuring out how to get their rockets back down to Kerbin safely, the research engineers at FLOOYD were quickly realising that protecting parts on ascent was just as important. Heavy research into two-dimensional-input driven procedural construction was then funded with the hopes of making protective shells for important payloads and interstage areas of the crafts. The protective shells also have the benefit of making the craft more aerodynamic, hopefully saving on precious rocket fuel! The AE-FF3 is the largest size available from FLOOYD. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXTfairingSize5
Title: AE-FF5 Airstream Protective Shell (5m)
Description: While the Kerbals at Mission Control were still figuring out how to get their rockets back down to Kerbin safely, the research engineers at FLOOYD were quickly realising that protecting parts on ascent was just as important. Heavy research into two-dimensional-input driven procedural construction was then funded with the hopes of making protective shells for important payloads and interstage areas of the crafts. The protective shells also have the benefit of making the craft more aerodynamic, hopefully saving on precious rocket fuel! The AE-FF5 is the largest size available from FLOOYD. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXTfloatFront
Title: LF-01A Sea-Float End
Description: A pointy end for the LF-01B. Makes sea-floats look more floaty. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXTfloatMid
Title: LF-01B Sea-Float Midsection
Description: Lets face it, we've all tried ditching a plane in the water. Doesn't always go too well does it. That's where the LF-01B comes in. Big and empty, the LF-01B is excellent at displacing fluids and bobbing around in the water. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXTfloatOutboard
Title: LF-01B Sea-Float Outrigger
Description: Used to stabilise seaplanes. Strangely wings don't react well to water at 50m/s. Who'd have guessed. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXTFuel625m
Title: Mk1 LFO Barrel
Description: Less 'High tech spaceship part', more 'We spent the budget on food and this was the only thing we could find lying around'. The designers did manage to add a smaller sub-tank for oxidiser, although the words 'plastic bag - Oxidiser goes here' can be seen on the blueprints. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RO BUT PLACED AND COSTED BY RP-0)

Name: SXTGoose
Title: M-95 "Goose" Cockpit
Description: An uncharacteristic foray into airliner control systems from Probodobodyne, the Goose provides a reliable avionics base and a 3 person crew for longer range flights and extra nap time. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXTHECSRanger
Title: Mariner Core
Description: Probe core used for early Ranger missions as well as (in stripped-down form)  the first Mariner missions. Includes data storage for returning data to Earth (use Ship Manifest to transfer the data from the experiment to this core).

Name: SXTInlineAirIntake
Title: XM-600 1.25m Air Intake
Description: Vac-Co's answer to C7 Aerospace's Circular Turboprop intake. Slightly less efficient, but slightly lighter. Plus it has a spinny-round bit.

Name: SXTInlineAirIntakeTLarge
Title: XM-800 2.5m Air Intake
Description: Designed on the principle of 'what if', no doubt high dangerous for any pilot if a cockpit is mounted to the fore. (Missing entryCost field) (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXTISSHabISK30
Title: Skylab Orbital Workshop
Description: Hold 8 peole with 155 days (5 months) of supplies. A large crew compartment designed for larger, more permanent space stations. Designed and launched in 1973, the Skylab orbital station was the wider space station ever. Given the 270m3 pressurised volume, there is plenty of room for all your IVA activies. It even features a orbital laboratory!

Name: SXTJ213
Title: Junkers Jumo 213E
Description: WWII-era V-12 liquid-cooled piston engine, the Jumo 213E as produced by Junkers (GER).  3-speed, 2-stage supercharger (only mid and high blowers modelled) intended for performance at high altitudes.  Used on the Focke-wulfe Fw 190 D-11, D-12, D-13 and Focke-wulfe Ta 152 fighters. 2050PS.

Name: SXTK1Base5m
Title: N1 Block B
Description: N1 Block B is second stage of N1. Block B has 8 NK-15V engines. Diameter: [10.3 m].

Name: SXTK1BaseLarge
Title: N1 Block A
Description: N1 Block A is first stage of N1. Block A has 30x NK-15 or NK-33 engines. Diameter: [17.0 m]. (PART NOT COSTED BY RP-0 BUT IN CORRECT NODE)

Name: SXTK1Decoupler
Title: N-1 Block B/V Interstage
Description: Install between 2nd and 3rd stages

Name: SXTK1Decoupler2
Title: N-1 Block A/B Decoupler
Description: Install between 1st ans 2nd stages.

Name: SXTKD170
Title: RD-170 Series
Description: 1980s to present, High TWR, atmospheric booster engine. The RD-170 is the most powerful liquid rocket engine ever flown. Originally developed for the Energia launcher's boosters, the engine consists of four combustion chambers fed by a single turbopump. A modified version, the RD-171, is used on the first stage of the Zenit launch vehicle. Diameter: [3.8 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: SXTKDBTsar1
Title: Kerbolyov 'Tsar V' Large Fuel Tank
Description: [SXT/Parts/SuperLaunchers/Hull/Tsar/3-75-0.cfg] (Missing entryCost field) (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXTKDBTsar2
Title: N-1 Block B
Description: Stores fuel for Block B.

Name: SXTKDBTsar25to375
Title: N-1 Block V
Description: Stores fuel and avionics for the N-1 Block V.

Name: SXTKDBTsar3
Title: N-1 Block A
Description: Stores fuel for Block A

Name: SXTke111
Title: Heinkel He 111 cockpit
Description: Constructed originally for the German Heinkel He 111 type bomber, this cockpit is useful for airdrop carrier planes, reconnaisance craft, and other vehicles where high visibility is paramount.

Name: SXTKe90TurboJet
Title: Progress D-18T turbofan
Description: High-bypass turbofan for An-225 and An-124. 229.8kN thrust, SFC 0.360 lb/lbf hr.

Name: SXTKO211Dprop
Title: Junkers Jumo 211F
Description: WWII-era V-12 liquid-cooled piston engine, the Jumo 211F as produced by Junkers (GER).  2-speed, 1-stage supercharger.  Used on the He 111.

Name: SXTKO211prop
Title: KO-A601 "Monsoon" Prop Engine
Description: A slight increase in power and efficiency over the KO-211D, however, this necessitated a larger and heavier casing. Requires 60 units Liquid Fuel per hour at maximum throttle. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXTKOPO4E
Title: Kopo-4e "Pancake" Liquid Fuel Engine
Description: The KDB's contender for a 2.5m orbital rocket engine. While less powerful that Rockomax's "Poodle", its lower profile and strengthened casing does make it easier to land on if you happen to forget your landing legs. Plume configured by RealPlume. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXTLANCER
Title: CR-9 L.A.N.C.E.R. Engine
Description: The L.A.N.C.E.R. is the result of the continuing joint venture between C7 Aerospace and the Rockomax Conglomerate. Designed to fill a gap in the design requirements for large sustainable single stage to orbit aircraft, this engine combines the best of rocket and air-breathing thrust technology. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXTLander
Title: PPD-8 Lander Can
Description: While similar to the Mk2 Lander Can internally, the PPD-8 offers a ruggedized casing and improved crash resistance, plus handy EVA hand grips. It can also be controlled remotely.

Name: SXTlaunchclamp1
Title: TT06-A Launch Stability Enhancer
Description: The TT06-A Stability Enhancer uses ground-breaking fastening technology to significantly increase the stability of spacecraft during the pre-launch phase. While OMB Demolition has been criticized in the past for using "big fancy words for a rocket holder" in their description of their device, none can say the TT18 series doesn't deliver rock-solid clamping action, as advertised. The owner's manual strongly suggests these devices be placed on the bottommost section of the spacecraft, and activated as soon as the engines are lit, for optimal de-clamping performance.

Name: SXTLT80
Title: J-2 Series
Description: The Rocketdyne J-2 rocket engine found on the Saturn S-IVB and S-II stages. Ensure you enable roll capability or disable gimbal as required for your application. Diameter: [2.01 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: SXTmeadowlark
Title: EAS-316 "Meadowlark" Observation Pod
Description: The EAS 316 is a lightweight observation pod that works in the same was as the EAS-1 External Command Seat. Features a 'No key' start button, though that just means that the pilots have normally gone back to the KSC to find the non-existent keys on launch. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXTMerlin46Prop
Title: Rolls-Royce Merlin 46
Description: WWII-era V-12 liquid-cooled piston engine. Provides 1260HP at sea level, rising to 1440HP at 4.42km (full throttle height). Single-speed single-stage supercharger. 10ft 11in 3-blade constant speed propeller.

Name: SXTMerlin66prop
Title: Rolls-Royce Merlin 66
Description: WWII-era V-12 liquid-cooled piston engine. Provides 1975HP at sea level, rising to 2020HP at 1.2km (full throttle height). Two-speed single-stage supercharger. 10ft 11in 3-blade constant speed propeller.  Used on Spitfire LF Mk VIII for low-altitude operations.

Name: SXTMiniJet
Title: Williams/Rolls-Royce FJ44-2A turbofan
Description: A Small civil turbofan

Name: SXTmk210degree
Title: Mk2 10-DEG Tilted connector
Description: For those times when you want your spaceplanes to have a bend before they hit the ground. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXTmk2225degree
Title: 22.5-DEG Tilted connector
Description: For those times when you want your spaceplanes to have a bend before they hit the ground. (Missing entryCost field) (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXTmk2adaptorIntake
Title: Mk2 to 1.25m "Su.27" Air Intake
Description: A generic Mk1 to Mk2 adapter that was almost sheared in two. We had to weld some intakes to it so it wouldn't fall apart. Erm, ahem, I mean we added intakes for extra utility and its structural integrity is second to none. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXTmk2cargoadapter
Title: Mk2 Cargo Bay CRG-04B
Description: A modification to the CRG-04, the B variant is inspired by the popular Mk2-Size 1 adaptor series. It also makes an excellent shroud for VTOL capable jet engines. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXTMk2FuselageStructural
Title: Structural Fuselage Mk2
Description: A standard Mk2 fuselage. Carries no fuel; is there merely as a structural element. As such, it's lighter and more solid due to reinforcements. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXTMk2LinearAerospike
Title: Mk2 "Stubbs" Linear Aerospike Engine
Description: A linear aerospike consists of a tapered wedge-shaped plate, with exhaust exiting on either side at the "thick" end. This design has the advantage of being stackable, allowing several smaller engines to be placed in a row to make one larger engine while allowing steering through the use of individual engine throttle control. Plume configured by RealPlume. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXTmk2SAScore
Title: Advanced Reaction Wheel Module, MK2
Description: While lacking the specialised pitch authority of the drone core, these wheels do provide more lateral and roll control. The lack of an AI also makes this 95% less murderous. We're still investigating what's causing that other 5%. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXTmk3CargoBayRamp
Title: Mk3 Cargo Ramp
Description: A sophisticated deployment system for cargo delivery on the ground, or on the sea, or in mid-air, or in a vacuum. Wherever you want, really. (Missing entryCost field) (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXTmk3Cockpit52
Title: B-52 Stratofortress cockpit
Description: Cockpit for the B-52 Stratofortress, long-range, subsonic, jet-powered strategic bomber.

Name: SXTMTVGirder
Title: Strongback Truss (Closed Long)
Description: A long, structural strongback truss, perfect for landers.

Name: SXTMTVGirderBasic
Title: Strongback Truss (Closed Short)
Description: A short, structural strongback truss.

Name: SXTMTVGirderOpen
Title: Strongback Truss (Open Long)
Description: A long strongback truss for carrying cargo.

Name: SXTMTVGirderOpenMedium
Title: Strongback Truss (Open Medium)
Description: A medium length strongback truss for carrying cargo.

Name: SXTMTVGirderOpenSmall
Title: Strongback Truss (Open Short)
Description: A short strongback truss for carrying cargo.

Name: SXTn1GridFin
Title: N-1 Grid Fins
Description: Improves N-1 stability

Name: SXTNERVA
Title: Bimodal NTR
Description: Low thrust pump-fed expander nuclear engine. Evolved for the original NERVA design the Bimodal NTR, instead of wasting precious propellant mass for cooling the engine reactor, uses a Brayton cycle electricity generator unit to convert the waste thermal energy into useful electrical power. It also supports liquid oxygen injection (TRITON - trimodal operation) for increased thrust but with the cost of a lower overall efficiency. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: SXTNERVAB
Title: NERVA II
Description: A later 70s atomic engine. Relatively low TWR but high ISP and power generation of 4200 MW. Derived from the Phoebus 2A ground demonstrator, tested in 1968. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: SXTNK12M
Title: KO-TP12M "Bear" Turboprop

Description: N1 Block V is third stage of N1. Block V has 4 NK-21 engines. Diameter: [7.7 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: SXTnuclearramjet
Title: LV-NRJ "Agamemnon" Nuclear Ramjet Engine
Description: The LV-NRJ is a Nuclear Ram-Jet, utilizing an unshielded nuclear reactor to heat incoming air. While it does not require fuel, it will need boosting to a suitable velocity before becoming effective. Despite being the result of many years of very expensive research, we're not entirely certain of the side-effects of using the engine - every scientist on the project has since turned a slightly more luminescent shade of green and expired. Plume configured by RealPlume. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXTOMS
Title: O-10 "Puff" Orbital Manoeuvering System

Name: SXTOMS-A
Title: O-40 "Puff" Orbital Manoeuvering System
Description: A more powerful RCS version of the Puff thruster, designed to stabalise the largest of rockets and shuttles. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXTProbeGooo

Name: SXTProtonlikeNoseCone
Title: Conformal Rocket Cone Mk3
Description: An elongated and slanted nose cone. Useful for solid rocket motors and other radially attached objects.

Name: SXTPWPT6
Title: Pratt & Whitney PT6A-15AG Turboprop
Description: Modern turboprop, 675 HP at takeoff

Name: SXTPWR2800
Title: Pratt & Whitney R-2800-63W Double Wasp
Description: 2200HP turbosupercharged radial with water injection 2600HP. Flat-rated to 8km with ram air and WEP, 9km dry. Used by P-47D-22.

Name: SXTR280018WProp
Title: Pratt & Whitney R-2800-18W Double Wasp
Description: WWII-era 2100HP (2450HP wet) twin-row 18-cylinder water-injected radial with a strong three-speed (only 2 modeled) two-stage supercharger. Note, due to modeling issues, will only develop rated altitude horsepower (high blower) when at maximum speed. Used on F4U-4 Corsair, XF6F-6 Hellcat, DC-6B.

Name: SXTR280021Prop
Title: Pratt & Whitney R-2800-21 Double Wasp
Description: 2000HP turbosupercharged radial. Nearly flat-rated until about 8.5km. 12ft 2in prop for high speeds.

Name: SXTRadialAirIntakeShockCone
Title: XF-104 Radial Air Intake
Description: Features a small shock-cone, allowing for better aircollection than the XM-G50 at high speeds.

Name: SXTradialFuel
Title: Boconok-9 Radial Fuel Tank & Heat Radiator
Description: Radial fuel container with built in radiator panels. The way we figure it, if we accidentally set the fuel on fire, the radiators will cool it down and everything will be fine. Hopefully. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXTradialWindow
Title: Airliner Window
Description: It's a window, you can look out of it. I wouldn't recommend it though, you might miss something on the TV.

Name: SXTRCSRack
Title: RCS Thruster 3x (1.24/2 kN class)
Description: A generic RCS thruster array. Use this for attitude control or translation/ullage for very large stages. Note that the thrust per nozzle is only one-third the thrust class
MOD: three nozzles fire in the same direction giving the class rating.

Name: SXTRotatingMk2Ring
Title: Centrifuge Habitat Mk2
Description: You know that moment when you realise the design for the new centrifuge didn't have that decimal place in. Yeah, that. Genuinely surprised no-one got fired.  An uncharacteristic foray into long-term habitation modules from C7 Aerospace, this centrifuge is most certainly the result of years of careful planning and analysis...definitely, not the result of an accidental bulk order of Mk2 crew cabins. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXTSaturnV1
Title: Kerbodyne S5-64000 Propellant Tank
Description: Kerbodyne's experimental ultra-heavy fuel tank. Do not smash a champaign bottle against the side. We did that once when launching a ship, it made a dent that would later lead to a catastrophic unplanned disassembly.

Name: SXTSaturnV1-2Sep
Title: TR-50B Stack Decoupler
Description: A stack separator for the truly massive 5m tank, allows extra space for mounting engines inside. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXTSaturnV1-2SepSmall

Description: A low profile stack separator for the truly massive 5m tank. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXTSaturnV1Base
Title: BZ-2500 Radial Attachment Point
Description: Perfect for mounting additional engines to even the largest of rockets. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: SXTSaturnV2
Title: Kerbodyne S5-32000 Propellant Tank
Description: Kerbodyne's experimental ultra-heavy fuel tank. Half the size of the S5-64000, I'd say it's twice as good, but it's not.

Name: SXTSaturnV2-3Sep

Name: SXTshockConeIntakeSize2

Name: SXTSize2SRB

Name: SXTsize2to3Adaptor

Name: SXTSputnik

Name: SXTTank1
Title: Kerbodyne S5-16000 Propellant Tank

Name: SXTTinyprop

Name: SXTTriangleRightangle

Name: taerobee_aerobee

Name: taerobee_control

Name: taerobee_decoupler

Name: taerobee_despin

Name: taerobee_largeFin

Name: taerobee_nosecone
