Name: tatsujin
Title: LM-DS Generic Spacecraft Bus
Description: A general purpose spacecraft bus. Example uses include the Mars Reconnaissance Orbiter (MRO), the Mars Atmosphere and Volatile EvolutioN (MAVEN), and the OSIRIS-REx missions.

Name: TD339
Title: TD-339
Description: The Vernier System as used on the Surveyor Probes. Uses storable hypergolic propellants, has infinite restarts and is not subject to ullage. Throttleable down to 30%. Historically 3 of them were used on the Surveyor probes which landed on the Moon. Diameter: [0.13 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: telescopicLadder
Title: Kelus Mobility Enhancer
Description: The Kelus Mobility Enhancer comes equipped with advanced telescopic extension technology. Recommended load 0.5 kerbals. After discovering that their name was already in use, Kelus picked their current name with the flip of a coin.

Name: telescopicLadderBay
Title: Kelus-LV Bay Mobility Enhancer
Description: The Kelus-LV Mobility Enhancer Bay comes equipped with advanced telescopic extension technology. Recommended load 1.5 kerbals. After discovering that their name was already in use, Kelus picked their current name with the flip of a coin.

Name: TESTMODULEADAPTER
Title: Logistics Module (Large)
Description: An extended general purpose cargo module for on-orbit operations.

Name: tg_bo
Title: Progress 7K-TG Orbital Module Probe
Description: Orbital module for the Progress 7K-TG.

Name: tg_sa
Title: Progress 7K series Instrument Module
Description: Instrument module for 7K series of Progress.

Name: TGWheel
Title: TG-Wheel
Description: This wheel for the little yellow trucks, with tiny combined power unit, retardation device and very limited vector control, gives just enough movement for you not to have to push....much (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: Thermometermt1
Title: AIES MT-1 Thermometer
Description: This superior device is used to measure the temperature. Like you don't know.

Name: THOR_ABLE_INT
Title: THOR ABLE Decoupler
Description: Interstage for the Thor/Able launch vehicle.

Name: THOR_ABLESTAR_INT
Title: THOR ABLESTAR Decoupler
Description: Interstage for the Thor/AbleStar launch vehicle.

Name: Thrustframe
Title: Thrust Frame
Description: An integrated heat shield and thrust frame used by many satellites and deep space probes to protect against the heat of the engine during burns, and also to transfer the thrust from the engine to the spacecraft structure.

Name: TinyTim
Title: Tiny Tim Booster
Description: Small solid fueled booster originally used to power anti-shipping missiles during WW2. Used as the kick stage on the WAC Corporal, the USA's first sounding rocket, and reused in modified form for the Aerobee line of sounding rockets. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: tiros-1
Title: Tiros-1 Satellite
Description: Tiros-1 weather satellite

Name: TITAN_III_INT
Title: TITAN IIIB Interstage
Description: Interstage for TITAN III launch vehciles.

Name: TITAN_IIIB_INT
Title: TITAN IIIB Interstage
Description: Interstage for TITAN 34D and TITAN III Commercial launch vehciles.

Name: TITAN_IV_INT
Title: TITAN IV Interstage
Description: Interstage for TITAN IV launch vehicle.

Name: TitanIUpper
Title: Titan I Series Upper Stage Fuel Tank
Description: This fuel tank can be used for the upper stage in Titan I series builds. Also includes a radio guidance module.

Name: top500a1ur5
Title: AIES TOP-500B Fairing
Description: Aerodynamic fairings specifically designed for use in long and narrow designs.

Name: topb1
Title: AIES TOP-B1 Fairing
Description: It is a type of rather small fairing, used in a new type of rocket AIES known as mini rockets.

Name: torekka
Title: Voyager Core
Description: Avionics and control unit for the Voyager deep space probes.

Name: toroidalAerospike
Title: J-2T-200/250K
Description: Aerospike. Using proven technology from the J-2 and introducing an aerospike nozzle to the developing J-2S machinery. Diameter: [2.5 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: toroidalFuelTank
Title: ROUND-8 Toroidal Fuel Tank
Description: An unconventionally shaped (but undoubtedly handy) fuel tank.

Name: torpod
Title: AIES R350 'TOR' [1.0m]
Description: This small probe was designed to carry out very specialised government space projects, but as the market for space modules grew the 'downgraded consumer version' had to be introduced. Spy cameras are not included.

Name: TOWER_SOYUZ
Title: R7 Launch Gantry
Description: The launch pad for the R7 series rockets. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: Trainer?Cockpit
Title: F-104 Starfighter Cockpit
Description: It was originally supposed to be a cutting-edge cockpit for a next-gen mk2 stealth fighter, but after years of delays, budget overruns and re-resigns, the project manager finally had enough: "Just call it something and push it on the markets!". Then we ended up with this thing.

Name: transit2a
Title: Transit-2A Satellite
Description: Transit-2A Navy navigation satellite

Name: truss-circular-01
Title: Modular Multipurpose Annular Truss XL
Description: A gigantic truss suitable for all sorts of orbital construction. Contains multiple structural variants for infinite fun. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: truss-circular-02
Title: Modular Multipurpose Annular Truss
Description: A medium size but still impressive truss suitable for all sorts of orbital construction. Contains multiple structural variants for infinite fun. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: truss-circular-03
Title: Modular Multipurpose Annular Truss Mini
Description: A smallish but massive circular truss. Contains multiple structural variants for infinite fun. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: truss-circular-04
Title: Modular Multipurpose Annular Truss Micro
Description: A mini annular truss segment! It's so tiny we almost forgot that it's STILL HUGE. Contains multiple structural variants for infinite fun. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: truss-circular-adapter-01
Title: Modular Annular Truss Adapter
Description: Adapts a gigantic 5 meter truss mount to a 3.75m stack. Hollow, with an alternate version with a central truss (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: truss-circular-adapter-02
Title: Modular Annular Truss Adapter V2
Description: Adapts a gigantic 5 meter truss mount to a 3.75m stack in a very small space. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: truss-circular-docking-01
Title: Modular Annular Truss Docking Connector
Description: A high strength docking connector of significant size. Hollow! (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: truss-hex-01
Title: Modular Multipurpose Hexa-Girder L1
Description: A large truss piece that fits around 1.25m pieces. Multiple variants are available. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: truss-hex-02
Title: Modular Multipurpose Hexa-Girder M1
Description: A medium truss piece that fits around 1.25m pieces. Multiple variants are available. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: truss-hex-03
Title: Modular Multipurpose Hexa-Girder S1
Description: A wee truss piece that fits around 1.25m pieces. Multiple variants are available. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: truss-hex-adapter-01
Title: Modular Hexa-Girder Adapter
Description: Adapts a hexa truss connection to a 1.25m stack (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: truss-octo-01
Title: Modular Multipurpose Octo-Girder XL
Description: A large octagonal truss piece. Several variants are available with different structural and fuel configurations. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: truss-octo-02
Title: Modular Multipurpose Octo-Girder
Description: A medium octagonal truss piece. Several variants are available with different structural and fuel configurations. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: truss-octo-03
Title: Modular Multipurpose Octo-Girder Micro
Description: A small octagonal truss piece. Several variants are available with different structural configurations. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: truss-octo-04
Title: Modular Multipurpose Octo-Girder Nano
Description: A teensy octagonal truss piece. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: truss-octo-adapter-01
Title: Modular Octo-Girder Adapter
Description: Connect an octo-truss to a 2.5m part, you say? No problem! (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: truss-octo-adapter-crew-01
Title: Modular Pressurized Octo-Girder Adapter
Description: Connect an octo-truss to a 2.5m part - without letting out all the air - you meant to say? No problem! (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: truss-octo-angled-01
Title: Modular Octo-Girder Angular Connector
Description: A specialized angled octo-girder, available in angular increments of 90, 45 and 30 degrees. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: truss-octo-angled-crew-01
Title: Pressurized Modular Octo-Girder Angular Connector
Description: A specialized angled octo-girder, available in angular increments of 90, 45 and 30 degrees. This model is pressurized and allows crew passage. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: truss-octo-attach-01
Title: Modular Octo-Girder Radial Attach Node
Description: A radial attachment node that allows the Modular Octo-Girder to, quite literally, do anything. Two variants that work at 90 or 45 degrees to a standard truss. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: truss-octo-crew-01
Title: Modular Pressurized Octo-Girder XL
Description: A large octagonal truss piece with an integrated pressurized section. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: truss-octo-crew-02
Title: Modular Pressurized Octo-Girder
Description: A medium octagonal truss piece with an integrated pressurized section. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: truss-octo-crew-03
Title: Modular Pressurized Octo-Girder Micro
Description: A small octagonal truss piece with an integrated pressurized section. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: truss-octo-docking-125
Title: Modular Octo-Girder Docking Connector
Description: A docking port compatible with the standard Clamp-O-Tron docking port. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: truss-octo-docking-25
Title: Modular Octo-Girder Heavy Docking Connector
Description: A heavier Modular Octo-Girder docking port. Compatible with the larger standard Clamp-O-Tron Senior docking port. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: truss-octo-docking-octo
Title: Modular Octagonal Docking Connector
Description: A docking port compatible uniquely with other octagonal docking connectors. Configured to lock solely at 90 degree increments for efficient construction. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: truss-octo-drone-01
Title: Modular Octo-Girder Guidance Unit
Description: Remotely operated guidance unit with the most advanced algorithms. Also incorporates a large, powerful set of reaction wheels suitable for moving large spacecraft. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: truss-octo-hub-01
Title: Modular Octo-Girder Octo-Hub
Description: This large structural hub expands the range of attachment options for octo-girders by six! (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: truss-octo-hub-crew-01
Title: Modular Pressurized Octo-Girder Octo-Hub
Description: Just like the modular octo-hub, but with an integrated pressurized segment. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: truss-spinal-01
Title: Modular Spinal Truss
Description: A large square truss of considerable size with an internal core. Available in several variants. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: truss-spinal-02
Title: Modular Spinal Truss Mini
Description: A medium square truss of considerable size with an internal core. Available in several variants. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: truss-spinal-03
Title: Modular Spinal Truss Micro
Description: A small square truss of considerable size with an internal core. Available in several variants. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: truss-spinal-adapter-01
Title: Modular Spinal Truss Series-3 Adapter
Description: Adapts the Spinal Truss profile to a standard 3.75m mount. Some variants are available. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: truss-spinal-adapter-02
Title: Modular Spinal Truss Series-2 Adapter
Description: Adapts the Spinal Truss profile to a standard 2.5m mount. Some variants are available. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: truss-spinal-docking-01
Title: Modular Spinal Truss Docking Connector
Description: A docking connector adapted for the spinal truss specification. Can lock to 90 degree increments. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: trussAdapter
Title: Modular Girder Adapter
Description: This piece allows you to attach Modular Girder parts to standard 1.25m attachment points.

Name: trussPiece1x
Title: Modular Girder Segment
Description: New! Build the structure of your dreams with the Maxo Construction Toys Modular Girder Segment!

Name: trussPiece3x
Title: Modular Girder Segment XL
Description: Now even bigger! Build larger structures of larger dreams!

Name: turboFanEngine
Title: J58-P-4
Description: Designed in the late 1950s, the J58 was redesigned and repurposed for one use: Mach 3+ aircraft like the A-12 / SR-71A/B / YF-12A. This model, the only operational one, entered service with the Blackbird in the mid 1960s. Variable CPR from 8.8 to 2.93 due to bypass vents progressively opening past Mach 2; fully open at Mach 3. 111.2kN dry. SFC 0.8/1.9 lb/lbf-hr static. Temperature limit Mach 4.1. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: turboFanSize2
Title: CF6-50E turbofan
Description: The CF6 series high bypass turbofan powers B747, B767, DC-10 and A300 civil aircraft. 233.5kN thrust, SFC 0.376 lb/lbf-hr. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: turboJet
Title: F100-PW-229 turbofan
Description: Pratt and Whitney F100 low-bypass turbofan with afterburner, used by F-15E/I/S and F-16C/D. Powered by NASA EngineSim. 129.4 kN wet, 79.2 kN dry. SFC 0.74/2.05 lb/lbf-hr static. Temperature limit Mach 2.85. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: Typhoon?Cockpit
Title: Mk1 Typhoon Cockpit
Description: Check your orbital trajectory and the name of the pilot while dodging missiles. Features air intakes under the nose for more compact design. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: UAEcubplate
Title: GEOStar-2 Satellite Bus
Description: Used in many communications satellite the GEOStar-2 satellite bus will be perfect for your medium sized builds.

Name: US_1C10_Wedge_Quadcore
Title: Universal Storage: QuadCore
Description: A central core that allows the attachment of four Universal Storage segments.

Name: US_1C15_Wedge_Hexacore
Title: Universal Storage: Hexacore
Description: With thin walls and a tiny service passage, the Hexacore is often touted as the central truss of an accident waiting to happen. Often purchased by desperate space agencies strapped for cash and common sense, this core represents a balancing act of price and functionality. Holds six wedges (reasonably well).

Name: US_1C20_Wedge_Octocore
Title: Universal Storage: Octocore
Description: A central core that allows the attachment of eight Universal Storage wedges.

Name: US_1M110_Wedge_ScienceBay
Title: Universal Storage: Science Bay
Description: Featuring revolutionary hinge technology gleaned from the cupboards under the sink; the Science Bay provides stowage for equipment deemed too sensitive to glue onto the outside of a spacecraft. With adequately filed edges and punchy caution stickers, EVA data retrieval has never been safer!

Name: US_1P110_Wedge_Fuelcell
Title: Universal Storage: Alkaline Fuel Cell
Description: This small fuel cell consumes hydrogen and oxygen to produce potable water, heat, and a moderate electrical output. Rated at 710W. Safer than having radioactive thermal generators on board. Small storage capacity for fuel and water biproduct.

Name: US_1P120_Wedge_Elektron
Title: Universal Storage: Elektron
Description: An ISS Elektron unit miniaturized to halve it's size and capacity. Provides breathable oxygen by breaking down water, but at the price of a massive electrical load.

Name: US_1R210_Wedge_Liquidfuel
Title: Universal Storage: LF10 Fuel Tank
Description: One big non-pressurized tank for all your fuel needs.

Name: US_1R220_Wedge_Monoprop
Title: Universal Storage: Pressurized Service Tank
Description: Nice round pressurized tank for just about anything.

Name: US_1R330_Wedge_Hydrogen
Title: Universal Storage: Hydrogen Tank
Description: Contains a large spherical canister of liquid hydrogen. Use with the fuel cell, or to inflate flammable exploding balloon animals. Please keep away from birthday candles or Jeb's ego.

Name: US_1R340_Wedge_Oxygen
Title: Universal Storage: Oxygen Tank
Description: Contains four individual liquid oxygen canisters. Separated to ensure redundancy in the unlikely event of explosion from external forces. Intended to provide resources for a fuel cell but can also be used to provide oxygen for life support. Licking the boil-off valve is discouraged.

Name: US_1R360_Wedge_Water
Title: Universal Storage: Water Tank
Description: One big water tank.

Name: US_2R340_Radial_Oxygen
Title: Universal Storage: Radial Oxygen Tank
Description: One external oxygen canister with its contents under pressure. Although holding much less gas than its cryogenic counterparts, it does help minimize weight, and helps to keep the workplace occupational hazard department off our backs.

Name: US_e_Dec_SafetyDecoupler250
Title: Universal Storage Decoupler: Large
Description: A specialized stack separator designed with crew safety in mind. Replacing explosive bolts with eight fail-safe pneumatic cylinders
MOD: this decoupler cannot be staged by overeager ground staff and must be activated by direct command of the crew.  Decoupling function currently disabled. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: US_f_Dec_SafetyDecoupler125
Title: Universal Storage Decoupler: Small
Description: A specialized stack separator designed with crew safety in mind. Replacing explosive bolts with eight fail-safe pneumatic cylinders
MOD: this decoupler cannot be staged by overeager ground staff and must be activated by direct command of the crew. Decoupling function currently disabled. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: US_Radial_R30_Water
Title: Universal Storage: Radial Water Tank
Description: A small and cheap water canister, the expendible nature of this tank often leads to its abuse at the hands of reckless LEM designers. Please refrain from using these tanks as landing gear. Drink responsibly.

Name: USRPWS
Title: Univ. Storage - RPWS Antenna
Description: The Radio and Plasma Wave Science instrument measures electrostatic and electromagnetic fields generated by the interaction of planetary magnetospheres and the interplanetary plasma medium. Deploy and use while in low to high orbit. Not for use during atmospheric flight or surface deployment. Use with New Horizon's Universal Storage system.

Name: utilityCabin
Title: PPD-24 Itinerant Service Container
Description: The Itinerant is a handy service compartment for use in deep space missions. It seats two Kerbals and includes a decent amount of built-in electric storage and a small radioisotope generator.

Name: V-1650-7
Title: Packard Merlin V-1650-7
Description: WWII-era V-12 liquid-cooled piston engine, the Merlin as produced by Packard (US). 1620HP at sea level with ram air with a very strong two-speed two-stage supercharger (1710 max with ram air at just over 3km, second peak 1410HP at 7.9km). 67inHG max boost. Used on the P-51B/C/D Mustang. 11ft 2in 4 blade constant speed propeller.

Name: vanguard-1
Title: Vanguard 1
Description: United States satellite Vanguard-1

Name: vanguard-2
Title: Vanguard 2
Description: United States satellite Vanguard-2

Name: vanguard-3
Title: Vanguard 3
Description: United States satellite Vanguard-3

Name: vasimr-0625
Title: VX-100 'Helicon' VASIMR Plasma Thruster [Test]
Description: Based on the Ad Astra lab test article built to test the configuration to be flown on the ISS, the VASIMR engine is far more powerful than any other ion engine to this point. It will require about 100kW of power. NOTE: This is a lab test article, flight hardware may differ from this device.

Name: vasimr-125
Title: VW-200 'Magnotron' VASIMR Plasma Thruster [Extrapolated]
Description: A paired VX-100 engine with the same variable thrust and fuel use abilities. The invention of insulated wires has allowed some increase in capabilities.

Name: vasimr-25
Title: VW-10K 'Cyclotron' VASIMR Plasma Engine [Extrapolated]
Description: Our scientists inform us that the 10K stands for an idea, rather than any particular ability to do 10,000 of anything. This engine is nevertheless very powerful, being composed of several ultra-high-power variable plasma thrusters. May require advanced power generation technology to run.

Name: Vega_Stage1
Title: Vega Stage 1 (P80)
Description: The P80 is a solid fuel booster based on the Ariane 5 EAP.

Name: Vega_Stage2
Title: Vega Stage 2 (Zefiro 23)
Description: The second stage of Vega is also a solid fuel booster.

Name: Vega_Stage3
Title: Vega Dtage 3 (Zefiro 9)
Description: The Zefiro 9 is a copy of the second stage.

Name: Vega_Stage4
Title: Vega Stage 4 (AVUM)
Description: The Vega upper stage is a liquid fuel engine.

Name: VegaFairing
Title: Vega fairing
Description: A small fairing for small payloads.

Name: vernierEngine
Title: Conformal RCS Thruster (275/445 N class)
Description: A generic conformal RCS thruster. Use this for attitude control or translation/ullage for spaceplanes. LEO-rated heat shielding.

Name: VR1vulcan
Title: RS-68 Series
Description: 1990s Medium TWR atmospheric engine. Using technology developed for the Space Shuttle SSME, the RS-68 is a single-use engine, featuring a simplified design with less parts and an easier construction. The RS-68 powers the Delta IV launch vehicle family and is the most powerful LH2/LOX engine ever flown. Exhaust from the gas generator is used for roll control. Diameter: [2.43 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: WBI_ATVSeat
Title: ATV Command Seat
Description: This bare-bones seat gives you just enough flight controls to externally control a vessel without those cumbersome inconveniences like a "pressurized cabin" and "seat belts."

Name: WBI_AuxEN
Title: Auxiliary Electronic Navigatior
Description: The Auxiliary Electronic Navigator (AuxEN) is a specialized chassis segment that contains a probe core. Simply orient the section of the box that says "Front" on it forward, and clip it into your chassis.

Name: WBI_Buckboard
Title: MC-1000 Buckboard
Description: Essentially a redesigned SC-62 Standard Container, The Buckboard can hold a wide variety of different resources. It's essential equipment for the kerbal on the go.

Name: WBI_Buckboard2
Title: MC-2000 Buckboard
Description: For those kerbals that have more stuff than fits in a standard storage box, this double-length Buckboard gives you more room. Of course, empty space needs filling, so it's an endless cycle of getting more room and then filling it..

Name: WBI_Buckboard3
Title: MC-3000 Buckboard
Description: Designers took a look at the MC-2000 with envy and created this larger MC-3000, a triple-length version of the SC-62-derived MC-1000. Now you have even more storage to fill up!

Name: WBI_Buckboard4
Title: MC-6000 Buckboard
Description: Especially designed to lose your luggage, the Bucboard 6000 provides a significant amount of storage. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: WBI_BuffaloAdapter
Title: Buffalo Adapter
Description: This small adapter provides a streamlined transition from the Buffalo cab form factor to the 1.25m standard hull size.

Name: WBI_BuffaloAeroCone
Title: Buffalo Type 2 Cone
Description: This aero cone is angled like the nose of the Buffalo command cab and has a small storage hold. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: WBI_BuffaloAeroCone1
Title: Buffalo Type 1 Cone
Description: This is a basic cone to meet your fashion needs. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: WBI_BuffaloAeroCone3
Title: Buffalo Type 3 Cone
Description: This cone is pointy and has a sizeable storage hold. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: WBI_BuffaloAeroCone4
Title: Buffalo Type 4 Cone
Description: This cone is pointy and has a sizeable storage hold. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: WBI_BuffaloAirlock
Title: Buffalo Airlock Module
Description: The Buffalo Airlock Module (BAM) provides a handy location to perform EVAs from- and to take the brunt of impacts when backing up. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: WBI_BuffaloCab
Title: Buffalo Command Cab
Description: The cornerstone of the Modular Space Exploration Vehicle (MSEV), the Buffalo Command Cab provides command and control functionality for the MSEV system. The Buffalo Command Cab seats two kerbals, albeit in a confined space.

Name: WBI_BuffaloDrill
Title: Buffalo Drill
Description: Extract valuable resources from the crusts of planets and asteroids by drilling into the ground. An internal auger moves the regolith to holding tanks for later processing. When operated by a skilled engineer, you will be able to operate with better efficiency.  These modules operate best at their ideal operating temperatures, and features auto-shutdown in the event of excessive overheating.  Radiators can be used to help manage excessive heat. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: WBI_BuffaloGroundStabilizer
Title: Buffalo Ground Stabilizer
Description: The ground stabilizer keeps your rovers stable while doing important things like loading and unloading cargo. It also includes SAS and can be used as a docking port. Careful design of your rovers (attach the chassis after assembling the body components) will ensure that your cabs will be docked and undocked properly. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: WBI_BuffaloISRU
Title: Buffalo ISRU
Description: A smaller version of Kerbodyne's mobile processing plant, this module can take raw materials containing even trace amounts of oxygen and hydrogen, and crack them into useful fuel products. While this smaller model is lighter than it's bigger cousin, it is less efficient, and not designed for long-term operations. These modules operate best at their ideal operating temperatures, and features auto-shutdown in the event of excessive overheating. Radiators can be used to help manage excessive heat. This particular model was rebuilt from a prototype. It can be configured to produce a variety of different resources. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: WBI_BuffaloPowerPack
Title: Flex Fuel Power Pack
Description: The Flex Fuel Power Pack can run off of different fuels, albeit with different efficiencies, with LiquidFuel/Oxidizer offering the best power generation. It even has a set of solar panels for auxilary power. To change the fuel type after launch, be sure to go on EVA. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: WBI_BuffaloSaddleTank
Title: Buffalo Saddle Tank
Description: Attach this tank to the side of your Buffalo, and you can hold additional resources. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: WBI_BuffaloSAS
Title: Buffalo SAS Module
Description: The Buffalo SAS Module has an array of reaction wheels. These spin very quickly to create torque without wasting propellant. These large wheels are driven by proportionally larger electric motors, so keep an eye on your ElectricCharge levels. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: WBI_BuffaloWingType1
Title: Type 1 Buffalo Wing
Description: This part is either a vaguely wing-shaped plank or a giant surfboard. We're not sure which. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: WBI_BuffaloWingType2
Title: Type 2 Buffalo Wing
Description: This part is either a vaguely wing-shaped plank or a giant surfboard. We're not sure which. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: WBI_BuffaloWingType3
Title: Type 3 Buffalo Wing
Description: This part is either a vaguely wing-shaped plank or a giant surfboard. We're not sure which. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: WBI_BuffaloWingType4
Title: Type 4 Buffalo Wing
Description: This part is either a vaguely wing-shaped plank or a giant surfboard. We're not sure which. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: WBI_CargoRamp
Title: Buffalo Cargo Ramp
Description: The Buffalo Cargo Ramp provides an easy way to walk your cargo onto a flat bed or service bay. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: WBI_Chassis1u
Title: Buffalo Chassis (1U)
Description: This sturdy chassis is designed to support a variety of components including the Buffalo Command Cab, and wheels. It also contains a battery pack.

Name: WBI_Chassis2u
Title: Buffalo Chassis (2U)
Description: This sturdy chassis is designed to support a variety of components including the Buffalo Command Cab, and wheels. It also contains a battery pack.

Name: WBI_Chassis3u
Title: Buffalo Chassis (3U)
Description: This sturdy chassis is designed to support a variety of components including the Buffalo Command Cab, and wheels. It also contains a battery pack, though field upgrades can enable it to hold a variety of different resources. This particular version is three times the length of the standard Chassis unit. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: WBI_ChassisDecoupler
Title: Chassis Decoupler
Description: While the Buffalo Cab is well suited for standard decouplers, the question of how to mount an MSEV to a rocket via the chassis is answered with the chassis decoupler. This specialized decoupler attaches one end to a rocket and the other end to a chassis.

Name: WBI_ChassisEndu
Title: Buffalo Chassis (End)
Description: This sturdy chassis is designed to support a variety of components including the Buffalo Command Cab, and wheels. This end unit has no storage capacity but it provides a nice bookend to a chassis.

Name: WBI_ChassisSlim2u
Title: Buffalo Slim-Chassis (2U)
Description: This sturdy chassis is half the width of a standard 2U chassis, perfect for fitting wheels into rovers able to drive out of cargo bays. It contains an integrated solar panel and a battery pack, though field upgrades can enable it to hold a variety of different resources. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: WBI_CrewCab
Title: Buffalo Crew Cabin
Description: The Buffalo Crew Cabin provides mobile living quarters for two kerbals. The facilities are pretty spartan, and the crew have to rearrange the furnature to take care of their basic necessities. It still beats the confines of the Buffalo Command Cab, and smells better too. The cabin also doubles as a small geo-survey lab once technology advances enough.

Name: WBI_Flatbed1uStd
Title: Buffalo Flatbed (1U)
Description: The Standard Flatbed is mounted to the Buffalo Chassis. It provides two hardpoints to mount a variety of equipment such as the Buckboard and Ponderosa. While you need an engineer to attach the flatbed to the chassis, you don't need one to stack equipment.

Name: WBI_Flatbed1uWide
Title: Buffalo Flatbed Wide (1U)
Description: The Wide Flatbed is mounted to the Buffalo Chassis. It provides three hardpoints to mount a variety of equipment such as the Buckboard and Ponderosa. While you need an engineer to attach the flatbed to the chassis, you don't need one to stack equipment.

Name: WBI_Flatbed2uStd
Title: Buffalo Flatbed (2U)
Description: The Standard Flatbed is mounted to the Buffalo Chassis. The 2u simplifies construction a bit by doubling the length of the flatbed. It provides four hardpoints to mount a variety of equipment such as the Buckboard and Ponderosa. While you need an engineer to attach the flatbed to the chassis, you don't need one to stack equipment.

Name: WBI_Flatbed2uWide
Title: Buffalo Flatbed Wide (2U)
Description: The Standard Flatbed is mounted to the Buffalo Chassis. The 2u simplifies construction a bit by doubling the length of the flatbed. It provides six hardpoints to mount a variety of equipment such as the Buckboard and Ponderosa. While you need an engineer to attach the flatbed to the chassis, you don't need one to stack equipment.

Name: WBI_GrapplerArm
Title: Buffalo Grappler Arm
Description: Whether you're grabbing asteroids, vessels, or kerbals, the Grappler Arm is for you. Simply bolt one to your craft, arm it, and fly towards the target of your choice. WARNING: do not back objects into an armed grappler, or you'll tempt the Kraken!

Name: WBI_HalfChassis
Title: Buffalo Half-Chassis
Description: This sturdy chassis is half the size of a standard chassis. It contains an integrated solar panel and a battery pack.

Name: WBI_HalfServiceBay
Title: Buffalo Half-Service Bay
Description: The Half-Service Bay provides space to attach small parts such as science equipment. It has a central rack that can be installed before flight or in the field, and it has just enough room for one Buckboard 1000 storage containers. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: WBI_JetWing
Title: JetWing
Description: Created by pioneer Yves Kerman, the JetWing can trace its lineage back to the KQ-1 winged jetpack. The modern JetWing gives the power of flight to an individual kerbal crazy enough to wear a tiny set of wings and jet engines. Its vertical take off and landing (VTOL) hover capability and stability assist make it easy to fly. The engines can run on any world with an atmosphere thanks to its monopropellant fuel, but it comes at the expense of endurance. Or, switch over to liquid fuel and fly on worlds with oxygenated atmosphers with increased endurance. With a proper inventory system, the JetWing can be refueled simply by bolting it to the side of a craft and performing a standard fuel transfer. And don't forget the JetWing accessories... (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: WBI_JumpChute
Title: JetWing Parachute
Description: For the safety conscious, the JetWing Parachute offers a way back to the ground that doesn't involve a sudden stop at the end. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: WBI_JWCargoPallet
Title: JetWing Cargo Pallet
Description: This small cargo pallet can be attached to the JetWing's hardpoints and used to surface-attach small equipment. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: WBI_JWDropTank
Title: JetWing Drop Tank
Description: Need a little extra fuel? The JetWing Drop Tank provides exactly that. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: WBI_LongPassengerCab
Title: Long Passenger Cab
Description: This no-frills cabin holds four passengers in relative comfort. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: WBI_M1A0Wheel
Title: M1-A0 Bear Cub
Description: This adorable wheel is great for small rovers. While not particularly fast, the Bear Cub is rather portable.

Name: WBI_M1A2Wheel
Title: M1-A2 Grizzly
Description: Building upon their experience with the M1A1 Mountain Goat, Wild Blue Industries created the M1-A2 Grizzly heavy duty wheel. The Grizzly offers a wider wheelbase, lower center of gravity, faster speed and better traction than the Mountain Goat. Unfortunately, rovers built with these wheels will not be able to enter or exit Mk3 cargo bays.

Name: WBI_MicroJetEngine
Title: WJ400 Jaguar
Description: Sometimes you need a bit more thrust to carry those heavy payloads. The WJ400 Jaguar is a micro-jet engine that fits the bill. While it generates a tiny amount of thrust compared to other jet engines, the Jaguar's specialized electronics give it a hover mode that's tied to other hover-capable engines on the craft. It also can switch between liquid fuel for oxygenated atmospheres and monopropellant on worlds with atmospheres for reduced range. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: WBI_Mineshaft
Title: Mineshaft Portable Crew Tube
Description: Want to hop into another module without going EVA? Then the Mineshaft is for you. Simply attach one of these to each module you want to connect to, then run the tube between the Mineshafts. Canaries not included. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: WBI_OmniWheel
Title: M1-A1 Mountain Goat
Description: Wild Blue Industries is proud to offer the M1A1 Mountain Goat, also known as the Omni Wheel. When coupled with the Buffalo Half-Chassis, the M1-A1 is great for building rovers that can enter and exit the Mk3 cargo bays. Just orient the half-chassis so that it is the length of a normal chassis, and attach your wheels. Additionally, the ability to eject the wheels is useful for moving a base module into place and then setting it on the ground.

Name: WBI_Outback
Title: Outback ESP
Description: Sometimes you just need a small pack to carry a handful of items, and the Outback fits the bill. This handy Extravehicular Support Pack (ESP) offers a convenient space to store your stuff along with some extra EVA propellant for a longer ride. Use "X" to detach from the ship's hull, and "H" to attach it again.

Name: WBI_PlasmaTV
Title: Plasma TV - Small
Description: Unlike the DSEV graphene radiator, the plasma screen tv can actually display images. It's perfect for giving your intrepid crew the ability to see around their ship when stuffed in the back of a cargo bay, or for just watching an in-flight movie so they don't get bored.

Name: WBI_PlasmaTV2
Title: Plasma TV - Medium
Description: Unlike the DSEV graphene radiator, the plasma screen tv can actually display images. It's perfect for giving your intrepid crew the ability to see around their ship when stuffed in the back of a cargo bay, or for just watching an in-flight movie so they don't get bored.

Name: WBI_PlasmaTV3
Title: Plasma TV - Large
Description: Unlike the DSEV graphene radiator, the plasma screen tv can actually display images. It's perfect for giving your intrepid crew the ability to see around their ship when stuffed in the back of a cargo bay, or for just watching an in-flight movie so they don't get bored.

Name: WBI_QuarterChassis
Title: Buffalo Quarter-Chassis
Description: This sturdy chassis is one-quarter the size of a standard chassis. Why such a small chassis section exists is rather puzzling. Perhaps it works best with really small rovers. It contains an integrated solar panel and a battery pack.

Name: WBI_RadialEngineMount
Title: Radial Engine Decoupler
Description: For those times when you need some way to radially attach rocket engines and fuel tanks, and then have them detach, the Radial Engine Mount is the part for you. Do not stand directly behind the Radial Engine Mount. Not responsible for kerbals that go flying when you stand directly behind the Radial Engine Mount. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: WBI_RCS5Way
Title: Mk1 5-Way RCS Thruster
Description: This 5-way RCS thruster is perfect for small craft that just need a little push. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: WBI_RCS5Way2
Title: Mk2 5-Way RCS Thruster
Description: This 5-way RCS thruster also has a built-in monopropellant engine that delivers a small amount of thrust. It also has probe core functionality for VTOL flights. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: WBI_RCSCompressedAir
Title: Compressed Air RCS Thruster
Description: This 5-way RCS thruster is perfect for small craft that just need a little push. It runs on CompressedAir instead of Monopropellant. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: WBI_RCSModule
Title: RCS Module
Description: This powerful RCS thruster module also provides reaction wheel control and "turbo boost" engines for jumping. It also has a small chassis spacer that you can add/remove before flight. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: WBI_SAFER
Title: S.A.F.E.R.
Description: The Safe Affordable Fission Engine with Radiators (SAFER) generates copious amounts of power for your spacecraft and installation needs. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: WBI_ScannerArm
Title: Buffalo A.R.C.S. Arm
Description: The Asteroid Resource Composition Scanner (ARCS) is specially designed for scanning asteroids for their resource content. Simply point it at an asteroid you're attached to, turn it on, and read the composition report.

Name: WBI_SCPAdapter
Title: SCPAdapter
Description: For the fashion conscious, this simple adapter connects 1.25m diameter parts with the 1m diameter standard crew port found on the Buffalo Crew Module and the Pathfinder-line of inflatable modules. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: WBI_ServiceBay
Title: Buffalo Service Bay
Description: The Service Bay provides space to attach small parts such as science equipment. It has a central rack that can be installed before flight or in the field, and it has just enough room for one Buckboard 2000 or a pair of Buckboard 1000 storage containers. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: WBI_ShortPassengerCab
Title: Short Passenger Cab
Description: This no-frills cabin holds two passengers in relative comfort. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: WBI_SolarFlatbed1u
Title: Buffalo Solar Flatbed (1U)
Description: The Solar Flatbed takes the flatbed concept a step further by integrating ruggedized solar panels to generate electrical charge. Just don't place anything on them or they won't generate power. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: WBI_SolarFlatbed1uWide
Title: Buffalo Solar Flatbed Wide (1U)
Description: The Solar Flatbed takes the flatbed concept a step further by integrating ruggedized solar panels to generate electrical charge. Just don't place anything on them or they won't generate power. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: WBI_SolarFlatbed2u
Title: Buffalo Solar Flatbed (2U)
Description: The Solar Flatbed takes the flatbed concept a step further by integrating ruggedized solar panels to generate electrical charge. Just don't place anything on them or they won't generate power. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: WBI_SolarFlatbed2uWide
Title: Buffalo Solar Flatbed Wide (2U)
Description: The Solar Flatbed takes the flatbed concept a step further by integrating ruggedized solar panels to generate electrical charge. Just don't place anything on them or they won't generate power. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: WBI_TrailerHitch2
Title: Buffalo Trailer Hitch
Description: Want to drag a trailer across the globe? The Trailer Hitch is for you. simply dock with another trailer hitch and off you go. The trailer hitch also has a deployable ladder and two standard pipe connectors. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: WBI_Tundra200
Title: Tundra 200
Description: The Tundra 200 provides modular fuel storage conforming to the Buffalo standard form factor.

Name: WBI_Tundra400
Title: Tundra 400
Description: The Tundra 400 provides modular fuel storage conforming to the Buffalo standard form factor.

Name: WBI_Wagon2u
Title: Wagon
Description: The Wagon is a Buffalo Storage Module that's capable of holding a variety of items.

Name: WBI_WheelJack
Title: Wheel Jack
Description: Not to be confused with a transforming robot that was voiced by a famous actor, the wheel jack serves as the foundation for building a Buffalo MSEV. Simply bolt it into the ground. If you can run into the wheel jack and move it, then it's not bolted properly. Once bolted firmly into the ground, attach a Buffalo Assembly Port to the WheelJack's top node (be sure that the Assembly Port's RED side is up). Then attach the chassis or other components to the Buffalo Assembly Port. Finally, to detach the assembled vehicle, switch to the space center and back to the rover, then decouple the Assembly Port.

Name: WBI_WingRoot
Title: Buffalo Wing Root
Description: Specially designed for the Buffalo form factor, the wing root provides a handy location to attach wings to, and has some storage space. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: WBIFlightControlDummy
Title: Flight Control Upgrade
Description: This is a dummy part for flight control upgrades. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: WBITiltRotor
Title: WB-22 "Typhoon" Tiltrotor
Description: The tiltrotor engine is great for VTOL aircraft. It can pivot upwards, forwards, and backwards as needed. Its powerful electric motors allow for fast response to throttle commands but the motors require enormous amounts of electric charge. Best of all, the Typhoon's prop-rotors can be folded up for compact storage. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: WBITiltRotor2
Title: WB-44 "Hurricane" Tiltrotor
Description: The heavy-lift tiltrotor engine is great for VTOL aircraft. It can pivot upwards, forwards, and backwards as needed. Its powerful electric motors allow for fast response to throttle commands but the motors require enormous amounts of electric charge. Best of all, the Typhoon's prop-rotors can be folded up for compact storage. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: wheelMed
Title: TR-2L Ruggedized Vehicular Wheel
Description: The TR-2L is an extremely tough wheel made for mobilizing medium sized vehicles across a large variety of terrain. The extremely high traction tread ensures firm grip on any surface, providing reliability and reducing the chances of being used for high-speed tomfoolery.

Name: wingConnector
Title: Wing Connector Type A
Description: A vaguely wing shaped board. Use at your own risk.

Name: wingConnector2
Title: Wing Connector Type B
Description: A vaguely wing shaped board. Use at your own risk.

Name: wingConnector3
Title: Wing Connector Type C
Description: A vaguely wing shaped board.

Name: wingConnector4
Title: Wing Connector Type D
Description: Found in a trash bin next to a wing factory.

Name: wingConnector5
Title: Wing Connector Type E
Description: Found in a trash bin next to a wing factory.

Name: WingGemini
Title: Gemini Wings
Description: The Winged Gemini experiment was designed so that Gemini could land on a runway. It would have greatly reduced the cost of recovery, but it was so unstable and hard to control in tests that it was abandoned.  See if you can do better! Make sure you come in nose first, if you start to spin turn off SAS and you will eventually recover, maybe. Also you will have very little control until you get to the thicker part of the atmosphere keep it nose down as long as possible to keep your speed up. Your glide slope should be very steep.

Name: WingGeminiContSurf
Title: Gemini Winged Control Surface
Description: Helps Gemini fly!  Put two of these stubby little control surfaces on the bottom of the Gemini wing.

Name: WingGeminiFP
Title: Gemini Winged Flight Pack
Description: Decoupler, and SAS flight pack for Winged Gemini.  This pack has a decoupler on the bottom to jettison spent fuel tanks or engines.

Name: WingGeminiFPContSurf
Title: Gemini Winged Flight Pack Control Surface
Description: It's not really a control surface, its more of a metal slat that deflects some of the air that goes by. Goes on the Gemini Flight Pack over the holes...

Name: winglet
Title: AV-T1 Winglet
Description: Nothing is really known about this thing. Use it at your own risk.

Name: winglet3
Title: Delta-Deluxe Winglet
Description: The Delta-Deluxe Winglet is a large aerodynamic surface with a small built-in aileron. It is very lightweight and offers more lift than the AV-R8 but the small control surface area means it is not as quick to turn.

Name: wingShuttleDelta
Title: Big-S Delta Wing
Description: The Big-S line of wings are C7's largest lifting surfaces to date. Not only are they Sturdy and heat resistant enough to survive reentry, but also have enough internal volume to carry optional fuel tanks.

Name: wingShuttleElevon1
Title: Big-S Elevon 1
Description: The Big-S line of wings are C7's largest lifting surfaces to date. Not only are they Sturdy and heat resistant enough to survive reentry, but also have enough internal volume to carry optional fuel tanks.

Name: wingShuttleElevon2
Title: Big-S Elevon 2
Description: The Big-S line of wings are C7's largest lifting surfaces to date. Not only are they Sturdy and heat resistant enough to survive reentry, but also have enough internal volume to carry optional fuel tanks.

Name: wingShuttleRudder
Title: Big-S Spaceplane Tail Fin
Description: Large heat resistant spaceplane fin.

Name: wingShuttleStrake
Title: Big-S Wing Strake
Description: The Big-S line of wings are C7's largest lifting surfaces to date. Not only are they Sturdy and heat resistant enough to survive reentry, but also have enough internal volume to carry optional fuel tanks.

Name: wingStrake
Title: Wing Strake
Description: Strakes are like sideburns for your plane. The girls will fall for you!

Name: X-405H
Title: X-405H
Description: Engine for proposed Vega stage for NASA Atlas-Vega LV. Superceded by Atlas-Agena once NASA became aware of the USAF's Agena stage.

Name: X1_Body
Title: X-1 Rocket Propellant Tank A
Description: A rocket propellant tank designed for aircraft.

Name: X1_Crew
Title: X-1 Cockpit
Description: Validated for flight at speeds exceeding 400 m/s, the X-1 is an ideal choice for supersonic vehicles.

Name: X1_Engine
Title: XLR11
Description: While it doesn't look a thing like it, this model represents the Reaction Motors XLR11, the first liquid fueled rocket engine designed for airplanes. Powered the X-1. Diameter: [0.46 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: X1_Tail
Title: X-1 Rocket Propellant Tank B
Description: A rocket propellant tank designed for aircraft, it's cone shaped too!

Name: X2009RCSX
Title: Orion MPCV RCS Thruster (Radial)
Description: Linear RCS thruster pod, each containing two R-1E thrusters. Originally developed for the Constellation CEV as auxiliary thrusters for orbital maneuvers and as a backup for the main engine.

Name: x2MNode1x
Title: Exploration Station Core Hub
Description: Station core hub for deep space exploration with four docking node attachment points.

Name: x2MSleepH3abV4-2x
Title: Exploration Station Habitat
Description: A habitation module for the Exploration Station.

Name: X84NEWTALUSXX2
Title: Interstage Adapter - SLS Block IB/II
Description: The structural adapter and explosive cord decoupler for the Exploration Upper Stage (EUS).

Name: Xafa191m23312NTR
Title: RL - II Propellant Tank
Description: A generic pressurized propellant tank for surface habitation modules.

Name: xALCOR_LanderCapsulex
Title: MMSEV Crew Cabin
Description: The MMSEV (Multi - Mission Space Exploration Vehicle) is a pressurized cabin exploration vehicle for either space or surface application. Features an airlock and a travel endurance for up to 10 kilometers.

Name: XAltair2descent2stageX
Title: Altair Descent Module
Description: Altair (or Lunar Surface Access Module - LSAM) was a Constellation program asset designed for Moon landings. The descent module would be used to capture into a lunar orbit, undock from Orion and then land on the surface. Payload includes either a crewed outpost or cargo. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: XATVpanel
Title: Orion MPCV Solar Array Wing (SAW)
Description: Derived from the solar arrays of the (now defunct) Automatic Transfer Vehicle (ATV) resupply spacecraft. Conversion efficiency has been improved from 11% to 16% and it is now able to supply up to 2.75 kW of electrical power. 14.25 m2.

Name: XB9_Utility_Light_N1_WhiteX
Title: N1 Utility Light
Description: A light source optimized for the rigors of space.

Name: xbahars68bx
Title: RS-68 Series
Description: 1990s Medium TWR atmospheric engine. Using technology developed for the Space Shuttle SSME, the RS-68 is a single-use engine, featuring a simplified design with less parts and an easier construction. The RS-68 powers the Delta IV launch vehicle family and is the most powerful LH2/LOX engine ever flown. Exhaust from the gas generator is used for roll control. Diameter: [2.43 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: xcstparachutex
Title: Orion Parachute Pack
Description: The main parachute pack for the Orion command module.

Name: XCXA_ACBMX
Title: Common Berthing Mechanism (CBM)
Description: A berthing mechanism used by the ISS modules (non Russian), the Multipurpose Logistics Modules (MPLM) and the resupply vehicles.

Name: XCXA_P6_BATTERY_TRUSSX
Title: CHAKA / Truss - Integrated Equipment Assembly
Description: A rigid,lightweight truss segment developed as part of the Integrated Truss System (ITS). This truss includes integral electrical equipment such as batteries, battery chargers/dischargers, DC switching units, and DC-DC converters. Additionally this truss segment includes a pump flow control assembly for any thermal control system radiators which may be attached. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: XCXA_P6_LONG_SPACERX
Title: CHAKA / Truss - Long Spacer (ITS)
Description: A rigid,lightweight truss segment developed as part of the Integrated Truss System (ITS). (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: xCXA_SAWx
Title: Expanded Solar Array Wing (SAW)
Description: A high power, steerable and retractable solar array wing for demanding payloads, similar to the ones used by the International Space Station (ISS). 96 m2.

Name: xCXA_Z1x
Title: CHAKA / Truss - Z1
Description: The stepping stone truss that serves as a temporary mounting point for structural and pressurized assemblies on a station. Complete with integral reaction wheels to give a nudge without having to burn up RCS. Trus has been fitted with a built-in probe unit and a battery reserve. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: XDRAGON--ADAPTERX
Title: Interstage Adapter - Delta IV DCSS (4 m)
Description: The structural adapter and explosive cord decoupler for the 4 meter Delta Cryogenic Second Stage (DCSS).

Name: XDragon2NoseConeX
Title: NDS Protective Nose Cone
Description: An aerodynamic nose cone for the NASA Docking System.

Name: xDragonLadderx
Title: Dragon Mobility Enhancer
Description: A low profile mobility enhancement system.

Name: xEMLVFX
Title: Payload Fairing - Delta IV [Procedural]
Description: A composite fairing that protects the payload from aerodynamic forces and heating during the launch and ascent phases of the flight.

Name: xEMLVKosmos_URM_Fairing_Conic_Salt
Title: Payload Fairing - Vulcan [Procedural]
Description: A composite fairing that protects the payload from aerodynamic forces and heating during the launch and ascent phases of the flight.

Name: xenon-125-1
Title: XE-400 Electric Propulsion Tank
Description: They told us we were crazy to need this much propellant. Well, maybe we were. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: xenon-125-2
Title: XE-200 Electric Propulsion Tank
Description: The attractive grey sheen of Probodobodyne's medium electric propulsion line delights amateur, enthusiast and professional alike.

Name: xenon-125-3
Title: XE-100 Electric Propulsion Tank
Description: When we approached Probodyne about a new, bigger electric propulsion container, they didn't believe us at first. So they sent this tiny thing! Still, we've found a use for it. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: xenon-25-1
Title: XE-P06 Electric Propulsion Tank
Description: Tank size watchers everywhere agree that this assembly of tanks is the most mass efficient electric propulsion tank out there, due to its use of many small pressure vessels. Allegations of suboptimal volume utilization are vigorously denied by Probodobodyne Inc. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: xenon-25-2
Title: XE-P04 Electric Propulsion Tank
Description: Another smash hit by Probodobodyne Inc., accomplished with nothing but a set of box cutters and some duct tape.

Name: xenon-25-3
Title: XE-P02 Electric Propulsion Tank
Description: A smallish set of eight tanks, built with Probodobodyne's meticulous attention to detail and hard work by its extensive QA division. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: xenon-radial-125-1
Title: XE-R04 Electric Propulsion Tank
Description: A nice replacement for that wee cylindrical tank Probodobodyne makes, this spherized super-tank can be radially attached for all your noble, gaseous needs. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

Name: xenonTank
Title: PB-X150 Xenon Container
Description: Although most of the Probodobodyne staff couldn't pronounce "Xenon", when told how to say it correctly, they all agreed it sounded super-cool - and everything possible should be done so it could be used as a fuel, no matter the cost.

Name: xenonTankLarge
Title: PB-X750 Xenon Container
Description: Although most of the Probodobodyne staff couldn't pronounce "Xenon", when told how to say it correctly, they all agreed it sounded super-cool - and everything possible should be done so it could be used as a fuel, no matter the cost.

Name: xenonTankRadial
Title: PB-X50R Xenon Container
Description: The X50R is a small-volume Xenon container, heralded by engineers for being ideally suited for small ion-driven spacecraft, and also for having thoroughly disproved management in their notion that a smaller fuel tank would make the fuel cheaper.

Name: XESARCSX
Title: Orion MPCV RCS Thruster (Inline)
Description: Linear RCS thruster pod, each containing two R-4D-11 thrusters. Originally designed by Marquardt for use on the Apollo Service Module, the Lunar Ascent and Descent modules and as a satellite apogee motor. Later variants were modified to support new propellant combinations and to increase the efficiency.

Name: XFASAApolloStrJ2StrJ23m5mDecX
Title: Orion MPCV Adapter
Description: A structural adapter for the Orion MPCV and the Service Module protection panels.

Name: XIUSLOWERXxxxtall
Title: Delta IV DCSS LOX Tank (5 Meters)
Description: This cryogenic liquid oxygen tank forms the lower portion of the 5 meter DCSS stage for the Delta IV family of launch vehicles.

Name: XIUSLOWERXxxxtall2G
Title: Delta IV DCSS LOX Tank (4 Meters)
Description: This cryogenic liquid oxygen tank forms the lower portion of the 4 meter DCSS stage for the Delta IV family of launch vehicles.

Name: XKarmonyStorModule_AdapterS6632
Title: Exploration Station Laboratory
Description: A research laboratory module for on-orbit operations.

Name: XKK_SPX_F9_OctawebX
Title: Falcon 9 Engine Mount
Description: The engine mount structure for the nine Merlin engines that power the first stage of the Falcon 9 launch vehicle.

Name: XKKLEGX
Title: Falcon 9 Landing Gear
Description: The landing gear for the SpaceX Falcon 9 launch vehicle.

Name: XKosmos_Angara_RD-275KX
Title: RD-253/RD-275
Description: A high thrust engine designed for use with storable propellants. In use with the Proton series of rockets. Diameter: [2.0 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: xKosmos_Balka_1_Tunnelx
Title: Exploration Station Crew Tunnel
Description: A structural tunnel for crew transfer for linking living quarters.

Name: xKosmos_SepRetrox
Title: SEP - 100 Separation Motor
Description: A generic solid rocket motor for safe separation of discarded rocket stages. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: xKosmos_SepRetroxMLS
Title: SEP - 50 Separation Motor
Description: A generic solid rocket motor for safe separation of discarded rocket stages. Plume configured by RealPlume.

Name: XKosmos_Strut_ConnectorX
Title: Universal Structural Connector
Description: General structural re-enforcement for space exploration vehicles.

Name: xKosmos_TKS_RCS_Tankx
